ALIYUN::MNS::Queue.Description: ALIYUN::MNS::Queue is used to create a queue to contain messages. Queues can be classified into standard and delayed queues.

DelaySeconds.Description:
It is measured in seconds. All messages sent to the queue can be consumed until the DelaySeconds expires.
An integer between 0 and 604800 (7 days). The default value is 0

PollingWaitSeconds.Description:
It is the maximum time that a ReceiveMessage request could be waiting for any incoming messages, while there are no message in the queue. Measured in seconds.
An integer between 0 and 30 seconds. The default value is 0 (seconds)

MessageRetentionPeriod.Description:
Maximum lifetime of the message in the queue, measured in seconds. After the time specified by this parameter expires, the message will be deleted no matter whether it has been consumed or not.
An integer between 60 (1 minute) and 1296000 (15 days). The default value is 345600 (4 days)

MaximumMessageSize.Description:
Maximum body length of a message sent to the queue, measured in bytes.
An integer between 1024 (1K) and 65536 (64K). The default value is 65536 (64K).

VisibilityTimeout.Description:
Duration in which a message stays in Inactive status after it is consumed from the queue. Measured in seconds.
An integer between 1 and 43200 (12 hours). The default value is 30 (seconds)

LoggingEnabled.Description:
Whether to enable log management. "true" indicates that log management is enabled, whereas "false" indicates that log management is disabled. 
The default value is false

ALIYUN::MNS::Subscription.Description: ALIYUN::MNS::Subscription is used to subscribe an endpoint to an Alibaba Cloud Message Service (MNS) topic. For a subscription to be created, the owner of the endpoint must confirm the subscription.

NotifyStrategy.Description:
Retry policy that will be applied when an error occurs during message push to the endpoint.
BACKOFF_RETRY or EXPONENTIAL_DECAY_RETRY; default value: BACKOFF_RETRY. For details about retry policies, refer to Basic Concepts/NotifyStrategy.

NotifyContentFormat.Description:
Format of the message content pushed to the endpoint.
XML, JSON, or SIMPLIFIED; default value: XML. For details about message formats, refer to Basic Concepts/NotifyContentFormat.

FilterTag.Description:
Message filter tag in the created subscription (Only messages with consistent tags are pushed.)
The value is a string of no more than 16 characters. The default value is no message filter.

ALIYUN::MNS::Topic.Description: ALIYUN::MNS::Topic is used to create a topic.

MaximumMessageSize.Description:
Maximum body length of a message sent to the topic, in the unit of bytes.
An integer in the range of 1,024 (1 KB) to 65, 536 (64 KB); default value: 65,536 (64 KB).

LoggingEnabled.Description:
Whether to enable log management. "true" indicates that log management is enabled, whereas "false" indicates that log management is disabled. 
The default value is false

AutoRenew.Description:
Specifies whether to enable auto renewal. Valid values:
true
false
Note Default value: false.

VSwitchId.Description: The ID of the VSwitch.

Period.Description:
The subscription period. You must specify this parameter if the value of the ChargeType
parameter is PrePaid. Unit: months. Valid values: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 12, 24,
and 36.
Note This parameter is invalid if the value of the ChargeType parameter is PostPaid.

InstanceClass.Description:
The instance type. For more information, see Instance types.
Note You need to pass at least one of the Capacity and InstanceClass parameters when calling
the CreateInstance operation.

VpcPasswordFree.Description:
Specifies whether to enable password free for access within the VPC. If set to:
- true: enables password free.
- false: disables password free.

InstanceName.Description:
The name of the instance. The name can be 2 to 128 characters in length and must start
with a letter. The following characters are not supported: at signs (@), forward slashes (/), colons (:), equal signs (=), double quotation marks
("), angle brackets (<>), braces ([]), curly brackets ({}) and spaces.

VpcId.Description: The ID of the VPC.

Capacity.Description:
The storage capacity of the instance. Unit: MB.
Note You need to pass at least one of the Capacity and InstanceClass parameters when calling
the CreateInstance operation.

AutoUseCoupon.Description:
Specifies whether to use a coupon. Valid values:
true
false
Note Default value: false.

ChargeType.Description:
The billing method of the instance. Valid values:
PrePaid: subscription.
PostPaid: pay-as-you-go.
Note Default value: PostPaid.

NetworkType.Description:
The network type of the instance. Valid values:
CLASSIC
VPC
Note Default value: CLASSIC.

PreferredBackupPeriod.Description: The backup cycle. Only for PostPaid instance. Valid values: Monday/Tuesday/Wednesday/Thursday/Friday/Saturday/Sunday

PreferredBackupTime.Description: The time period in which data is backed up. The time period must be in the HH:mmZ-HH:mmZ format.

EnableBackupLog.Description:
Enable or disable incremental backup. Options:
1, means open.
0, which means off, the default value.

Password.Description:
The password of the instance. The password can be 8 to 32 characters in length and
must contain at least three types of the following characters: uppercase letters,
lowercase letters, digits, and special characters. Special characters include ! at signs (@), number signs (#), dollar signs ($), percent signs (%), carets (^),
ampersands (&), asterisks (*), parentheses (()), underscores (_), plus signs (+),
hyphens (-), and equal signs (=).

ALIYUN::Memcache::Whitelist.Description: ALIYUN::Memcache::Whitelist is used to create a Whitelist.

SecurityIpGroupAttribute.Description: The default is empty. For distinguishing between different attribute values, the console will not display the value of hidden whitelist packet.

SecurityIps.Description: IP address whitelist to be modified

SecurityIpGroupAttribute.Description: The default is empty. For distinguishing between different attribute values, the console will not display the value of hidden whitelist packet.

SecurityIps.Description: IP address whitelist to be modified

ALIYUN::NAS::AccessGroup.Description: ALIYUN::NAS::AccessGroup is used to create a permission group.

AccessGroupType.Description: Permission group type, including the Vpc and Classic types

Description.Description: Permission group description. It is the same as the permission group name by default.

FileSystemType.Description:
File system type.
Values: standard (default), extreme

ALIYUN::NAS::AccessRule.Description: ALIYUN::NAS::AccessRule is used to create a rule for a permission group.

UserAccessType.Description: User permission type: no_squash (default), root_squash, all_squash

Priority.Description: Priority level. Range: 1-100. Default value: 1

FileSystemType.Description:
The type of file system. Values:
standard: the general NAS
extreme: the extreme NAS

Ipv6SourceCidrIp.Description:
Source IPv6 CIDR address segment. IP addresses in CIDR format and IPv6 format are supported.
Currently, only the ultra-fast NAS in mainland China supports the IPv6 function, and the file system needs to enable the IPv6 function.
Only VPC private network is supported.
IPv4 and IPv6 are mutually exclusive, and the types cannot be converted.

ALIYUN::NAS::DataFlow.Description: ALIYUN::NAS::DataFlow is used to create a data flow between a Cloud Parallel File Storage (CPFS) file system and an Object Storage Service (OSS) bucket.

SourceStorage.Description:
Access path stored at the source.Format: <storage Type>: // <PATH>.
in:
Storage Type: Currently only supports OSS.
PATH: OSS's bucket name.Limit the following.
Only support the lowercase letters, numbers and short strokes (-) and must start with a lowercase letter or number.
The length is 8 ~ 128 English characters.
Use UTF-8 encoding.
Can't start with http: // and https: //.
Explain that the OSS BUCKET must be the bucket that exists in the region.

Description.Description:
Description of data flow.
limit:
The length is 2 to 128 English or Chinese characters.
Start with a lowercase letter or Chinese, and you cannot start with http:// and https: //.
It can contain numbers, half-horn colon (:), down line (_) or short lines (-).

SourceSecurityType.Description:
The type of safety protection types of the source storage. If the source storage must be protected through safety protection, please specify the type of safety protection type storage.Value:
No (default value): It means that the source storage does not need to be accessed by safe protection.
SSL: Protective access through SSL certificates.

Throughput.Description:
The upper limit of transmission bandwidth for data flow, unit: MB/s.
Value: 
600
1200
1500

Explanation The transmission bandwidth of the data flow must be smaller than the IO bandwidth of the file system.

RefreshPath.Description:
Automatic update directory, data modification incident stored at the CPFS registration source end, check whether the source data in the directory is updated and automatically imported the updated data.
The default is empty. Any data update stored at the source will not automatically import the CPFS. You need to import and update through manual tasks.
limit:
The length is 2 to 1024 characters.
Use UTF-8 encoding.
It must start with a positive oblique line (/).
This directory must be existing directory on CPFS and must be located in the Fileset directory that flows in the data.

AutoRefreshPolicy.Description:
Automatic update strategy, after the source data is updated, the data update is introduced to the CPFS strategy.
None (default): The data update of the source is not automatically imported into CPFS. Users can import data update at the source end of the source through data flow tasks.
Importchanged: The data update at the source automatically imports CPFS.

AutoRefreshInterval.Description:
The automatic update interval time, every time the interval, the CPFS checks whether there is a data update in the directory. If there is data update, start the automatic update task, unit: minute.
Scope of value: 5 ~ 525600, default value: 10.

ALIYUN::NAS::FileSystem.Description: ALIYUN::NAS::FileSystem is used to create a file system in Apsara File Storage NAS (NAS).

FileSystemId.Description: ID of the file system created

Description.Description: File system description (space characters are not allowed)

StorageType.Description:
The storage type of the file System.
Valid values:
PerformanceCapacity(Available when the file_system_type is standard)
standardadvance(Available when the file_system_type is extreme)
advance_100advance_200(Available when the file_system_type is cpfs)

ZoneId.Description: Zone ID.

VSwitchId.Description: VSwitch ID.

Duration.Description:
The period of subscription in months. Required and valid when ChargeType is Subscription.
When the annual and monthly subscription instance expires without renewal, the instance will automatically expire and be released.

SnapshotId.Description: Snapshot ID.

DeletionForce.Description: Whether delete all mount targets on the file system and then delete file system. Default is false

EncryptType.Description:
Specifies whether to encrypt data. You can use keys that are hosted by Key Management Service (KMS) to encrypt data stored on a file system. Data is automatically decrypted when you access encrypted data. Valid values:
0: specifies that no encryption is applied to data on the file system.
1: specifies that encryption is applied to data on the file system.

VpcId.Description: Vpc ID.

Capacity.Description: File system capacity, the unit is GB. Required and valid when FileSystemType=extreme or cpfs.

ProtocolType.Description: Type of protocol used. Valid values: NFS, SMB, cpfs.

ChargeType.Description:
Type of payment:
PayAsYouGo (pay as you go)
Subscription

FileSystemType.Description: File system type. Allowed values: standard(default), extreme, cpfs

Bandwidth.Description: Maximum file system throughput, unit is MB/s. Required and valid only when FileSystemType=cpfs.

Tags.Description: Tags to attach to filesystem. Max support 20 tags to add during create filesystem. Each tag with two properties Key and Value, and Key is required.

ALIYUN::NAS::Fileset.Description: ALIYUN::NAS::Fileset is used to create a fileset.

FileSystemPath.Description:
The absolute path of Fileset to be created.
The parent catalog of specified the directory must be a directory in the file system.
The length is 2 to 1024 characters.
Specify the directory must start with positive (/).

Description.Description:
Fileset description information.
The length is 2 to 128 English or Chinese characters.
Start with a lowercase letter or Chinese, and you cannot start with http:// and https: //.
It can contain numbers, half-horn colon (:), down line (_) or short lines (-).

ALIYUN::NAS::MountTarget.Description: ALIYUN::NAS::MountTarget is used to create a mount target.

Status.Description: Status, including Active and Inactive

VpcId.Description: VPC network ID

NetworkType.Description: Network type, including Vpc and Classic networks.

SecurityGroupId.Description: Security group Id

VSwitchId.Description: VSwitch ID.

AccessGroupName.Description: Permission group name. Default to DEFAULT_VPC_GROUP_NAME.

EnableIpv6.Description:
Whether to create an IPv6 mount point.Value:
true: create
false (default): do not create
Note Currently, only the ultra-fast NAS in mainland China supports the IPv6 function, and the file system needs to enable the IPv6 function.

ALIYUN::NAS::ProtocolMountTarget.Description: ALIYUN::NAS::ProtocolMountTarget is used to create an export directory for a protocol service.

ExportId.Description: The protocol service exports directory ID.

FsetId.Description:
Fileset ID needs to be exported.
limit:
The Fileset must exist.
A Fileset allows only one export directory.
Fileset and Path can only specify one.

Path.Description:
The path of the CPFS directory that needs to be exported.
limit:
This directory must be existing directory on CPFS.
The same directory allows only one export.
Fileset and Path can only specify one.
Format:
The length is 1 to 1024 characters.
Use UTF-8 encoding.
It must start with the positive oblique line (/), and the root directory must be/.

Description.Description:
Description of the protocol service to export the directory.The console is displayed as the export directory name.
limit:
The length is 2 to 128 English or Chinese characters.
Start with a lowercase letter or Chinese, and you cannot start with http:// and https: //.
It can contain numbers, half-horn colon (:), down line (_) or short lines (-).

VpcId.Description: Proper network ID exported by the protocol service.

VSwitchId.Description: Switch ID exported by the protocol service.

AccessGroupName.Description:
The name of the permissions group.
Default value: DEFAULT_VPC_GROUP_NAME

ALIYUN::NAS::ProtocolService.Description: ALIYUN::NAS::ProtocolService is used to create a protocol service for a Cloud Paralleled File System (CPFS) file system.

Description.Description:
Description of protocol service.The console shows the "protocol service name".
limit:
The length is 2 to 128 English or Chinese characters.
Start with a lowercase letter or Chinese, and you cannot start with http:// and https: //.
It can contain numbers, half-horn colon (:), down line (_) or short lines (-).

VpcId.Description: The protocol service VPCID needs to be consistent with the file system VPC.

ProtocolType.Description:
The protocol type of agreement service.
Ranges:
NFS: Agreement service supports NFS protocol access.
The default value: NFS.

ProtocolSpec.Description: The spec of protocol service. Default: General. Values: General

VSwitchId.Description: Agreement service vswitchid.

Throughput.Description:
The bandwidth of the agreement service.
Unit: MB/S.

ALIYUN::NLB::Listener.Description: ALIYUN::NLB::Listener is used to create a listener.

ListenerPort.Description: Port of the listener,[0, 65535] the portRange setting need 0

Cps.Description: New connection rate limit of Instance

LoadBalancerId.Description: ID of the LoadBalancer

Mss.Description: Max length of the TCP packet

SecurityPolicyId.Description: Only valid for TcpSSL protocol monitoring

CaCertificateIds.Description: List of the ca certificate ids

SecSensorEnabled.Description: Whether to enable the second-level monitoring function

Enable.Description: Whether to start listener or not. Default True.

Tags.Description: Tags to attach to instance. Max support 20 tags to add during create instance. Each tag with two properties Key and Value, and Key is required.

ALIYUN::NLB::LoadBalancer.Description: ALIYUN::NLB::LoadBalancer is used to create a Network Load Balancer (NLB) instance.

AddressIpVersion.Description: The version of IP address that the NLB instance uses to provide services.

VpcId.Description: The ID of the virtual private cloud (VPC) where the NLB instance is deployed.

LoadBalancerId.Description: The ID of the NLB instance.

AddressType.Description: The type of IP address that the NLB instance uses to provide services.

DNSName.Description: The domain name of the NLB instance.

ZoneMappings.Description: The zones, vSwitches and addresses which are mapped to the zones.

LoadBalancerType.Description: The type of the NLB instance.

AddressIpVersion.Description: The version of IP address that the NLB instance uses to provide services.

ResourceGroupId.Description: The ID of the resource group.

LoadBalancerBillingConfig.Description: The configuration of the billing method.

PayType.Description: The billing method of the NLB instance.

ZoneMappings.Description: The zones and the vSwitches in the zones. You must specify at least two zones.

ZoneId.Description: The ID of the zone to which the NLB instance belongs.

VSwitchId.Description: The ID of the vSwitch in the zone. Each zone can contain only one vSwitch and one subnet.

AllocationId.Description: The ID of the elastic IP address (EIP) that is associated with the Internet-facing NLB instance.

EipType.Description:
The type of the EIP. Valid values:
- **Common**
- **Anycast**
**Note**: Only NLB instances in Hong Kong, China, support binding Anycast EIP.

LoadBalancerAddresses.Description: Load balancer addresses. This property has higher priority than AllocationId and EipType in ZoneMappings.

AllocationId.Description: The ID of the elastic IP address (EIP) that is associated with the Internet-facing NLB instance.

ModificationProtectionConfig.Description: The configuration of the configuration read-only mode.

Status.Description:
Specifies whether to enable the configuration read-only mode. Valid values:
NonProtection: does not enable the configuration read-only mode. You cannot set the Reason parameter. If the Reason parameter is set, the value is cleared.
ConsoleProtection: enables the configuration read-only mode. You can set the Reason parameter.

Reason.Description: The reason why the configuration read-only mode is enabled. The value must be 2 to 128 characters in length, and can contain letters, digits, periods (.), underscores (_), and hyphens (-). The value must start with a letter.

CrossZoneEnabled.Description: Whether enable cross zone. Default: true

LoadBalancerType.Description: The type of the NLB instance.

LoadBalancerName.Description:
The name of the NLB instance.
The name must be 2 to 128 characters in length, and can contain letters, digits, periods(.), underscores (_), and hyphens (-). The name must start with a letter.

DeletionProtectionConfig.Description: The configuration of the deletion protection feature.

Enabled.Description:
Specifies whether to enable deletion protection. Valid values:
true: yes
false (default): no

Reason.Description: The reason why the deletion protection feature is enabled or disabled. The value must be 2 to 128 characters in length, and can contain letters, digits, periods (.), underscores (_), and hyphens (-). The value must start with a letter.

VpcId.Description: The ID of the virtual private cloud (VPC) where the NLB instance is deployed.

TrafficAffinityEnabled.Description: Whether enable traffic affinity. Default: false

BandwidthPackageId.Description: Attach common bandwidth package to load balancer.

AddressType.Description:
The type of IP address that the NLB instance uses to provide services. Valid values:
Internet: The NLB instance uses a public IP address. The domain name of the NLB instance is resolved to the public IP address. Therefore, the NLB instance can be accessed over the Internet.
Intranet: The NLB instance uses a private IP address. The domain name of the NLB instance is resolved to the private IP address. Therefore, the NLB instance can be accessed over the VPC where the NLB instance is deployed.

Tags.Description: Tags to attach to instance. Max support 20 tags to add during create instance. Each tag with two properties Key and Value, and Key is required.

ALIYUN::NLB::SecurityGroupAttachment.Description: ALIYUN::NLB::SecurityGroupAttachment is used to bind a security group to a Network Load Balancer (NLB) instance.

LoadBalancerId.Description: The ID of the network-based server load balancer instance to be bound to the security group.

ALIYUN::NLB::SecurityPolicy.Description: ALIYUN::NLB::SecurityPolicy is used to create a custom security policy for a TCP/SSL listener.

SecurityPolicyId.Description: The ID of the security policy.

Ciphers.Description: TThe supported cipher suites, which are determined by the TLS protocol version. You can specify at most 32 cipher suites.

*.Description:
TLS 1.0 and TLS 1.1 support the following cipher suites:
ECDHE-ECDSA-AES128-SHA
ECDHE-ECDSA-AES256-SHA
ECDHE-RSA-AES128-SHA
ECDHE-RSA-AES256-SHA
AES128-SHA
AES256-SHA
DES-CBC3-SHA
TLS 1.2 supports the following cipher suites:
ECDHE-ECDSA-AES128-SHA
ECDHE-ECDSA-AES256-SHA
ECDHE-RSA-AES128-SHA
ECDHE-RSA-AES256-SHA
AES128-SHA
AES256-SHA
DES-CBC3-SHA
ECDHE-ECDSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256
ECDHE-ECDSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384
ECDHE-ECDSA-AES128-SHA256
ECDHE-ECDSA-AES256-SHA384
ECDHE-RSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256
ECDHE-RSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384
ECDHE-RSA-AES128-SHA256
ECDHE-RSA-AES256-SHA384
AES128-GCM-SHA256
AES256-GCM-SHA384
AES128-SHA256
AES256-SHA256
TLS 1.3 supports the following cipher suites:
TLS_AES_128_GCM_SHA256
TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384
TLS_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256
TLS_AES_128_CCM_SHA256
TLS_AES_128_CCM_8_SHA256

ResourceGroupId.Description: The ID of the resource group.

SecurityPolicyName.Description:
The name of the security policy.
The name must be 1 to 200 characters in length, and can contain letters, digits, periods (.), underscores (_), and hyphens (-).

TlsVersions.Description: The supported versions of the Transport Layer Security (TLS) protocol. Valid values: TLSv1.0, TLSv1.1, TLSv1.2, and TLSv1.3.

Tags.Description: Tags to attach to instance. Max support 20 tags to add during create instance. Each tag with two properties Key and Value, and Key is required.

ALIYUN::NLB::ServerGroup.Description: ALIYUN::NLB::ServerGroup is used to create a server group for a Network Load Balancer (NLB) instance.

ServerType.Description:
The type of the backend server. Valid values:
- **Ecs**: an ECS instance.
- **Eni**: an ENI.
- **Eci**: an elastic container instance.
- **Ip**: an IP address.

Description.Description: The description of the servers. The description must be 2 to 256 characters in length, and can contain letters, digits, commas (,), periods (.), semicolons (;), forward slashes (/), at signs (@), underscores (_), and hyphens (-).

ServerId.Description:
The ID of the server. You can specify at most 40 server IDs in each call.
If the server group type is **Instance**, set the ServerId parameter to the ID of an Elastic Compute Service (ECS) instance, an elastic network interface (ENI), or an elastic container instance. These backend servers are specified by **Ecs**, **Eni**, or **Eci**.
If the server group type is **Ip**, set the ServerId parameter to an IP address.

ServerIp.Description: The IP address of the server. If the server group type is **Ip**, ServerId is taken as the value of this parameter.

Port.Description:
The port used by the backend server. Valid values: 0 to 65535. Default value is 0.
When the server group enables full port forwarding, there is no need to specify a port when adding a backend server (0 is entered by default). NLB will forward traffic to the back-end server according to the frontend request port.

Weight.Description:
The weight of the backend server. Valid values: 0 to 100. Default value: 100.
If the weight of a backend server is set to 0, no requests are forwarded to the backend server.

PreserveClientIpEnabled.Description: Whether to enable the client address retention function

ConnectionDrainEnabled.Description: Whether to enable graceful connection interruption

VpcId.Description: ID of VPC

AnyPortEnabled.Description:
Specifies whether to enable all-port forwarding. Valid values:
true
false (default)

UnhealthyThreshold.Description: Determine the health check status of the backend server from success to fail.

HttpCheckMethod.Description: When the health check protocol is http or https type, the selected health check detection method

HealthyThreshold.Description: Determine the health check status of the backend server from fail to success.

HealthCheckConnectTimeout.Description: Maximum timeout for each health check response

Tags.Description: Tags to attach to instance. Max support 20 tags to add during create instance. Each tag with two properties Key and Value, and Key is required.

ALIYUN::NLPAUTOML::Dataset.Description: ALIYUN::NLPAUTOML::Dataset is used to create a dataset.

DatasetName.Description: The name of dataset. Cannot start with numbers and symbols, and the length cannot be greater than 32 characters.

ProjectId.Description: The ID of project. To create a dataset under a certain project, fill in the target project ID.

DatasetRecord.Description: Upload labeled data to the dataset.

ALIYUN::NLPAUTOML::Model.Description: ALIYUN::NLPAUTOML::Model is used to create a model.

DatasetIdList.Description: The uploaded dataset must be under the same project, and the total number of marked data is greater than or equal to 4.

TestDatasetIdList.Description: Test set ID list. Some models under text classification support adding test set data.

ProjectId.Description: The project id to which the model belongs

ModelType.Description:
The type of model. Please refer to the documentation for the parameter values corresponding to different types of models.
Using the specified model type under different project, and the backend will do the verification. If the model type does not exist under the project, it will prompt that the base model is not found

ALIYUN::NLPAUTOML::Project.Description: ALIYUN::NLPAUTOML::Project is used to create a project.

ProjectName.Description: The name of project. Cannot start with numbers and symbols, and the length cannot be greater than 32 characters.

ProjectType.Description: The type of nlp project. The following value is allowed: ner, textCategorybaseRelation, textMatching, sentimentAnalysis, resumeExtract, reviewAnalysis

ProjectDescription.Description: The description of project.Cannot start with numbers and symbols, and the length cannot be greater than 256 characters.

AppKey.Description: The app key of the project.

Description.Description: Description of the project.

Name.Description: Name of the project.

ALIYUN::OOS::DefaultPatchBaseline.Description: ALIYUN::OOS::DefaultPatchBaseline is used to register a default patch baseline.

UpdatedBy.Description: The user who last modified the patch baseline.

Description.Description: The description of the patch baseline.

CreatedBy.Description: The creator of the patch baseline.

UpdatedDate.Description: The time when the patch baseline was last modified.

PatchBaselineName.Description: The name of the patch baseline.

CreatedDate.Description: The time when the patch baseline was created.

OperationSystem.Description: The type of the operating system.

ApprovalRules.Description: The rules of scanning and installing patches for the specified operating system.

PatchBaselineId.Description: The ID of the patch baseline.

ShareType.Description: The share type of the patch baseline.

PatchBaselineName.Description: The name of the patch baseline.

ALIYUN::OOS::Execution.Description: ALIYUN::OOS::Execution is used to start an execution.

Status.Description: Execution status.

CurlCli.Description:
Convenience attribute, provides curl CLI command prefix, which can be used to notify oos execution instead of OOS API NotifyExecution.
You can notify approve to oos execution by adding --data-binary '{"data": {"NotifyType": "Approve"}}' 
For more parameters in data, refer to https://help.aliyun.com/document_detail/120777.html.
You can also notify execution via ROS API SignalResource. API parameters Status and UniqueId are ignored. Use API parameter Data to pass data.

WindowsCurlCli.Description:
Convenience attribute, provides curl CLI command prefix for Windows, which can be used to notify oos execution instead of OOS API NotifyExecution.
You can notify approve to oos execution by adding --data-binary "{\"data\": {\"NotifyType\": \"Approve\"}}" 
For more parameters in data, refer to https://help.aliyun.com/document_detail/120777.html.You can also notify execution via ROS API SignalResource. API parameters Status and UniqueId are ignored. Use API parameter Data to pass data.

PowerShellCurlCli.Description:
Convenience attribute, provides curl CLI command prefix for PowerShell, which can be used to notify oos execution instead of OOS API NotifyExecution.
You can notify approve to oos execution by adding -Body '{"data": {"NotifyType": "Approve"}}' 
For more parameters in data, refer to https://help.aliyun.com/document_detail/120777.html.You can also notify execution via ROS API SignalResource. API parameters Status and UniqueId are ignored. Use API parameter Data to pass data.

CancelOnDelete.Description: Whether to cancel execution for resource deletion, if the execution is not completed. Default to false.

Timeout.Description: Timeout seconds before the completion of execution. Default to 1800.

SuccessStatuses.Description:
It is used for ROS to judge if resource creation is successful.
Default to [Success].
ROS will wait util some status in SuccessStatuses or FailureStatuses.
FailureStatuses has higher priority.
Specified all statuses(Started,Queued,Running,Waiting,Success,Failed,Cancelled) if you do not want to wait for the completion of execution.

FailureStatuses.Description:
It is used for ROS to judge if resource creation fails.
Default to [Failed, Cancelled].
ROS will wait util some status in SuccessStatuses or FailureStatuses.
FailureStatuses has higher priority.

LoopMode.Description:
The loop mode of OOS Execution. Valid values:
- Automatic(Default): does not pause.
- FirstBatchPause: The first batch of pauses.
- EveryBatchPause: pause each batch.

Description.Description: The description of OOS Execution.

Parameters.Description: Parameters for the execution of template.

SafetyCheck.Description:
Security check mode. Allowed values:
- Skip: This option means that customers understand the risks, you can do anything without confirmation Action, no matter what the level of risk. It takes effect only if Mode is Automatic.
- ConfirmEveryHighRiskAction (default): This option would require customers to confirm each Action a high risk. NotifyExecution by calling customer interface to confirm or cancel.

ResourceGroupId.Description: Resource group id.

TemplateName.Description: Template name. Content is limited to letters, numbers, underlined, underline, the length of 200 characters.

TemplateVersion.Description: Version number of template. Default to the latest version.

Tags.Description: Tag value and the key mapping, the label of the key number can be up to 20.

CreatedBy.Description: The user who created the encryption parameter.

ResourceGroupId.Description: The ID of resource group.

SecretParameterName.Description: The name of the encryption parameter.

UpdatedDate.Description: The time when the encryption parameter was updated.

CreateTime.Description: The time when the encryption parameter was created.

KeyId.Description: The Customer Master Key (CMK) of Key Management Service (KMS) that is used to encrypt the parameter.

SecretParameterId.Description: The ID of the encryption parameter.

UpdatedBy.Description: The user who updated the encryption parameter.

Type.Description: The data type of the encryption parameter.

Constraints.Description: The constraints of the encryption parameter.

ParameterVersion.Description: The version number of the encryption parameter.

Constraints.Description: The constraints of the encryption parameter.

ALIYUN::OOS::StateConfiguration.Description: ALIYUN::OOS::StateConfiguration is used to create a desired-state configuration.

StateConfigurationId.Description: The ID of the desired-state configuration.

ConfigureMode.Description: The configuration mode. Valid values: ApplyOnce: The configuration is applied only once. After a configuration is updated, the new configuration is applied. ApplyAndMonitor: The configuration is applied only once. After the configuration is applied, the system only checks whether the configuration is migrated in the future. ApplyAndAutoCorrect: The configuration is always applied.

ScheduleExpression.Description: The schedule expression. The interval between two schedules must be a minimum of 30 minutes.

ScheduleType.Description: The schedule type. Set the value to rate.

Description.Description: The description of the desired-state configuration.

ResourceGroupId.Description: The resource group ID.

TemplateName.Description: The name of the template. The name must be 1 to 200 characters in length and can contain letters, digits, hyphens (-), and underscores (_).

TemplateVersion.Description: The version number of the template. If you do not specify this parameter, the latest version of the template is used.

Tags.Description: Tag value and the key mapping, the label of the key number can be up to 20.

ALIYUN::OOS::Template.Description: ALIYUN::OOS::Template is used to create a template.

ResourceGroupId.Description: Resource group id.

Content.Description: The content of the template. The template must be in the JSON or YAML format. Maximum size: 64 KB.

TemplateName.Description: The name of the template. The template name can be up to 200 characters in length. The name can contain letters, digits, hyphens (-), and underscores (_). It cannot start with ALIYUN, ACS, ALIBABA, or ALICLOUD.

Tags.Description: Tag value and the key mapping, the label of the key number can be up to 20.

ALIYUN::OSS::Bucket.Description: ALIYUN::OSS::Bucket is used to create an Object Storage Service (OSS) bucket.

DomainName.Description: The public DNS name of the specified bucket.

InternalDomainName.Description: The internal DNS name of the specified bucket.

Name.Description: The name of Bucket

EnableOssHdfsService.Description:
Whether enable OSS-HDFS service. 
**Note**: Once it's enabled, it can't be disabled again.

ResourceGroupId.Description: The resource group id.

StorageClass.Description: Specifies the storage class of the bucket. Default is "Standard".

RedundancyType.Description:
Specifies the data disaster recovery type of the storage space. The value range is as follows:
LRS (default): Local redundant LRS stores your data redundantly on different storage devices in the same availability zone, and can support data loss and normal access even when two storage devices are damaged concurrently.
ZRS: Intra-city redundant ZRS adopts a data redundancy storage mechanism in multiple availability zones (AZ), and stores user data redundantly in multiple availability zones in the same region. When an availability zone is unavailable, normal access to data can still be guaranteed.

LifecycleConfiguration.Description: Rules that define how oss bucket manages objects during their lifetime.

Rule.Description: Describes lifecycle rules for the oss bucket Lifecycle Configuration property.

ServerSideEncryptionConfiguration.Description: Specifies the bucket used to store the server-side encryption rule.

SSEAlgorithm.Description: Specifies the default server-side encryption method.

KMSMasterKeyID.Description: Specifies the CMK ID when the value of SSEAlgorithm is KMS and a specified CMK is used for encryption. If the value of SSEAlgorithm is not KMS, this element must be null.

Status.Description: Specifies the versioning state of a bucket. Valid values: Enabled and Suspended.

CORSConfiguration.Description: Rules that define cross-origin resource sharing of objects in this bucket.

CORSRule.Description: A set of origins and methods that you allow.

DeletionForce.Description: Whether force delete the relative objects in the bucket. Default value is false.

LoggingConfiguration.Description: Settings that defines where logs are stored.

TargetPrefix.Description: This element lets you specify a prefix for the objects that the log files will be stored.

TargetBucket.Description: Specifies the bucket where you want Aliyun OSS to store server access logs.

Tags.Description: Bucket tags in k-v pairs format.

ALIYUN::OSS::Directory.Description: ALIYUN::OSS::Directory is used to create a directory for a specified bucket.

DeletionForce.Description: Whether force delete the relative objects in the directory. Default value is false.

ALIYUN::OSS::Domain.Description: ALIYUN::OSS::Domain is used to bind a custom domain name.

ALIYUN::OTS::Instance.Description: ALIYUN::OTS::Instance is used to create a Tablestore instance.

Description.Description: Instance description.

Network.Description: Instance network type, default is NORMAL.

ClusterType.Description:
Cluster type, the default is SSD. 
This parameter specifies the specification of the ots instance.
 When the value is SSD, the ots instance is a high-performance instance.
 When the value is Hybid, the ots instance is a capacity instance

Tags.Description: Tags to attach to instance. Max support 5 tags to add during create instance. Each tag with two properties Key and Value, and Key is required.

ALIYUN::OTS::SearchIndex.Description: ALIYUN::OTS::SearchIndex is used to create a search index for a data table. You can create multiple search indexes for a data table.

InstanceName.Description: The name of the OTS instance in which table will locate.

TableName.Description: The table name of the OTS instance.

IsArray.Description:
This parameter specifies whether the column is an array. 
A value of true indicates that the column is an array. Data written to the column must be a JSON array. 
Example: ["a","b","c"]. You do not need to explicitly specify this parameter for NESTED columns because they are arrays.

EnableSortAndAgg.Description: This parameter specifies whether to enable sorting and aggregation for the column.

Store.Description:
This parameter specifies whether to store the values of the field in the search index. 
A value of true indicates that you can read the values of the field directly from the search index without the need to query the table. 
This configuration optimizes query performance.

Index.Description:
This parameter specifies whether to index the column. 
The default is true, which means to build an inverted index or a spatial index for the column; if it is set to false, the column will not be indexed.

Analyzer.Description:
This parameter specifies the tokenizer. 
You can specify this parameter if the column is a TEXT column. Type: AnalyzerType.

SubFieldSchemas.Description:
This parameter specifies the list of field schemas for subfields. 
If the column is a NESTED column, you must specify this parameter to configure the index types of subcolumns in the NESTED column.

IsArray.Description:
This parameter specifies whether the column is an array. 
A value of true indicates that the column is an array. Data written to the column must be a JSON array. 
Example: ["a","b","c"]. You do not need to explicitly specify this parameter for NESTED columns because they are arrays.

EnableSortAndAgg.Description: This parameter specifies whether to enable sorting and aggregation for the column.

Store.Description:
This parameter specifies whether to store the values of the field in the search index. 
A value of true indicates that you can read the values of the field directly from the search index without the need to query the table. 
This configuration optimizes query performance.

Index.Description:
This parameter specifies whether to index the column. 
The default is true, which means to build an inverted index or a spatial index for the column; if it is set to false, the column will not be indexed.

Analyzer.Description:
This parameter specifies the tokenizer. 
You can specify this parameter if the column is a TEXT column. Type: AnalyzerType.

FieldName.Description:
This parameter specifies the name of the field (column) to index. 
The field can be a primary key column or an attribute column.

FieldType.Description:
This parameter specifies the type of the field. Type: FieldType. 
For more information, see the description of field types for a search index.

FieldName.Description:
This parameter specifies the name of the field (column) to index. 
The field can be a primary key column or an attribute column.

FieldType.Description:
This parameter specifies the type of the field. Type: FieldType. 
For more information, see the description of field types for a search index.

IndexSort.Description:
This parameter specifies how data is sorted. 
By default, the data is sorted in the same way as the primary key of the table. 
If the search index contains NESTED fields, data is not sorted by default.

Sorters.Description:
This parameter specifies the sorting methods.  Valid values: 
- PrimaryKeySort: The index is sorted by primary key in ascending or descending order.
- FieldSort: The index is sorted by a specified column in ascending or descending order.

FieldSort.Description:
Sort by field value. 
Only fields that are indexed and have sorting and statistical aggregation functions enabled can be pre-sorted

SortMode.Description: Sorting method when there are multiple values in the field.

SortOrder.Description: The sort order can be sorted in ascending or descending order, the default is ascending(SortOrder.ASC).

PrimaryKeySort.Description: You can use PrimaryKeySort to sort the query result based on the order of primary key columns.

SortOrder.Description: The sort order can be sorted in ascending or descending order, the default is ascending(SortOrder.ASC).

ScoreSort.Description:
You can use ScoreSort to sort the query result by keyword relevance score. 
ScoreSort is applicable to scenarios such as full-text indexing. 
Note Note that you must set ScoreSort to sort the query result by keyword relevance score. Otherwise, the query result is sorted based on the value of the IndexSort field.

SortOrder.Description: The sort order can be sorted in ascending or descending order

GeoDistanceSort.Description: You can use GeoDistanceSort to sort the query result based on distances of geographical locations.

SortMode.Description: Sorting method when there are multiple values in the field.

SortOrder.Description: The sort order can be sorted in ascending or descending order

RoutingFields.Description:
You can use this advanced feature to customize routing fields. 
You can specify some primary key columns as routing fields. 
Tablestore distributes data that is written to a search index to different partitions based on the specified routing fields. 
The data with the same routing field values is distributed to the same data partition.

ALIYUN::OTS::Table.Description: ALIYUN::OTS::Table is used to create a table based on a specified schema.

InstanceName.Description: The name of the OTS instance in which table will locate.

TableName.Description: The table name of the OTS instance.

TimeToLive.Description: The retention time of data stored in this table (unit: second). The value maximum is 2147483647 and -1 means never expired. Default to -1.

MaxVersions.Description: The maximum number of versions stored in this table. The valid value is 1-2147483647. Default to 1.

SecondaryIndices.Description: The secondary indices of the table.

PrimaryKeys.Description: The primary keys of the index.

DeviationCellVersionInSec.Description: Maximum version deviation. The purpose is mainly to prohibit writing and expected large data, such as setting the deviation_cell_version_in_sec to 1000, and if the current timestamp is 10000, the timestamp range allowed to be written is [10000 - 1000, 10000 + 1000]. The valid value is 1-9223372036854775807. Defaults to 86400.

PrimaryKey.Description: It describes the attribute value of primary key. The number of primary_key should not be less than one and not be more than four.

Type.Description: Type for primary key. Only INTEGER, STRING or BINARY is allowed.

Name.Description: Name for primary key.

Type.Description: The type of the column.

Name.Description: The column name of the column.

ReservedThroughput.Description: The initial reserved read/write throughput setting of the table to be created, the reserved read throughput and reserved write throughput of any table cannot exceed 5000.

Read.Description: The read service capability unit consumed by this operation or the reserved read throughput of the table. Default to 0.

Write.Description: The write service capability unit consumed by this operation or the reserved write throughput of the table. Default to 0.

ALIYUN::OTS::VpcBinder.Description: ALIYUN::OTS::VpcBinder is used to bind a Tablestore instance to a virtual private cloud (VPC).

Domains.Description: The domain names used to access the OTS instance in the VPC.

Endpoints.Description: Private network addresses used to access the OTS instance in the VPC.

VpcId.Description: Vpc Id.

InstanceVpcName.Description: Custom name, need to be unique under the OTS instance.

Network.Description:
Instance network type. The values are as follows:
1, the NORMAL instance does not limit the source of the request. (Defaults)
2. A VPC instance only allows requests from all VPCs it is bound to.
3, VPC_CONSOLE instance only allows requests from the console and all VPCs it is bound to

ALIYUN::PAI::Dataset.Description: ALIYUN::PAI::Dataset is used to create a dataset.

Options.Description: The extended field, which is of the JsonString type.

Description.Description: Custom descriptions of datasets to distinguish between different datasets.

CreateTime.Description: The creation time of the resource.

SourceType.Description: The data source type. The default value is USER.

WorkspaceId.Description: The ID of the workspace where the dataset is located. For details about how to obtain the workspace ID, see [ListWorkspaces](~~ 449124 ~~).

Uri.Description: The Uri configuration sample is as follows:.

DatasetId.Description: The first ID of the resource.

OwnerId.Description: The ID of the primary account.

UserId.Description: The ID of the user to which the dataset belongs.

DataType.Description: The dataset type. The default value is COMMON.

Options.Description:
The extended field, which is of the JsonString type.
When DLC uses a dataset, you can specify the default Mount path for the dataset by configuring the mountPath field.

Description.Description: Custom descriptions of datasets to distinguish between different datasets.

Accessibility.Description:
Workspace visibility. The following values are supported:
- PRIVATE (default): indicates that the workspace is visible to itself and the administrator.
- PUBLIC: The workspace is visible to all users.

DatasetName.Description:
The name of the dataset. The naming rules are as follows:
- Start with a lowercase letter, uppercase letter, number, or Chinese.
- Can contain an underscore (_) or a dash (-).
- 1~127 characters in length.

SourceType.Description:
The data source type. The default value is USER. The following values are supported:
- PAI-PUBLIC-DATASET:PAI public dataset.
- ITAG: The dataset generated by the iTAG module annotation result.
- USER: The data set registered by the USER.

SourceId.Description:
The data source ID.
- When the SourceType is USER, SourceId can be customized.
- When SourceType is ITAG, that is, when the iTAG module labels the data set generated by the result, SourceId is the task ID of ITAG.
- When SourceType is PAI_PUBLIC_DATASET, that is, a dataset created using PAI public datasets, SourceId is empty by default.

DataSourceType.Description:
The data source type. The following values are supported:
- OSS: Alibaba Cloud Object Storage (OSS).
- NAS: Alibaba cloud file storage (NAS).

WorkspaceId.Description:
The ID of the workspace where the dataset is located. For details about how to obtain the workspace ID, see [ListWorkspaces](~~ 449124 ~~).
If this parameter is not configured, the default workspace is used. If the default workspace does not exist, an error is reported.

DataType.Description:
The dataset type. The default value is COMMON. The following values are supported:
- COMMON: COMMON.
- PIC: picture.
- TEXT: TEXT.
- VIDEO: VIDEO.
- AUDIO: AUDIO.

Uri.Description:
The Uri configuration sample is as follows:
- The data source type is OSS:'oss:// bucket.endpoint/object'
- The data source type is NAS:
The general NAS format is: 'nas://<nasfisid>.region/subpath/to/dir/';
CPFS1.0:'nas://<cpfs-fsid>.region/subpath/to/dir /';
CPFS2.0:'nas://<cpfs-fsid>.region/<protocolserviceid>/'.
CPFS1.0 and CPFS2.0 are distinguished by the format of fsid: CPFS1.0 is cpfs-<8-bit ascii characters>;CPFS2.0 is cpfs-<16 ascii characters>.

Property.Description:
The properties of the dataset. The following values are supported:
- FILE: FILE.
- DIRECTORY: folder.

ALIYUN::PAIDLC::Job.Description: ALIYUN::PAIDLC::Job is used to create a Machine Learning Platform for AI (PAI) job to run in a cluster.

JobId.Description: The task ID created this time.

ThirdpartyLibs.Description: Python third-party library list to be installed.

Options.Description: The additional configuration of this task can adjust some of the behavior of the mounting data source through this parameter.If the task has a data source that mounted the OSS type, you can cover the default parameters of the jinofs by configure the configuration of this parameter to fs.OSS.DOWNLOAD.CONCURRENCY = 4, fs.oss.download.queue.size = 16.

Priority.Description:
The priority of the task, optional parameter, default value 1, the range of parameter values is 1 ~ 9.in:
1 is the minimum priority.
9 is the highest priority.

JobMaxRunningTimeMinutes.Description: The longest running time is running, and the unit is minutes.

WorkspaceId.Description: Work space ID, how to get working space ID, see listworkSpaces.

CodeSource.Description: The code source used in this task.Before the mission node starts, the DLC will automatically download the code configured in the code source, and mount to the local directory of the container.

MountPath.Description: This task needs to be mounted, optional parameters, and the mounting path is configured in the default code source.

Commit.Description: This task needs to download the code Commit ID, optional parameters, and use the Commith configuration of the code source by default.

Branch.Description: When running this task, the branch of the cited code warehouse can be selected, and the configuration branch field can be used by default.

CodeSourceId.Description: Code source ID.How to get code source ID, see ListCodesources.

VpcId.Description: User VPC ID.

SecurityGroupId.Description: The ID of the user security group.

JobSpecs.Description:
Jobspecs describes various configurations of tasks during the mission, such as mirror address, start command, node resource statement, number of copies, etc.
The DLC task consists of different types of nodes. The same type of nodes have exactly the same configuration. This configuration is called a Jobspec. Jobspecs describes the configuration of all types of nodes and is the array of Jobspec.

Type.Description:
Type is closely related to Job Type, and different Job Types support different Worker Types.
TFJob: supports Chief, PS, Worker, Evaluator, GraphLearn
PyTorchJob: Support Worker, Master
XGBoostJob: support Worker, Master
The Master in PyTorchJob and XGBoostJob is optional; if the Master is not specified, the system will automatically regard the first Worker node as the Master node.

Image.Description:
The running image address of this type of Worker.
You can call ListImages to obtain the community and PAI-optimized images provided by the PAI platform. It is also possible to specify an image publicized by a third party.

UserCommand.Description: Start commands of all nodes in the task.

DataSources.Description: List of data source used for task operation.

MountPath.Description: This task needs to be mounted, optional parameters, and the mounting path is configured in the default code source.

DataSourceId.Description: The ID of the data source.How to view the data source ID, see ListDataSets.

JobType.Description: The type of job. Values: TFJob, PyTorchJob, XGBoostJob, OneFlowJob, ElasticBatch

ResourceId.Description:
Resource group ID, optional parameter.
The parameter value is empty indicating that submitted to the public resource group.
If the current working space has been bound to a proprietary resource group, you can specify the corresponding resource group ID here; how to create a proprietary resource group and inquire about the proprietary resource group ID, please refer to the preparation and management of the DLC resource group cluster.

ThirdpartyLibDir.Description: The name folder of the Requirements.txt file is located; before each node runs the specified usercommand, PAI -DLC will take the requirements.txt file from the specified folder and call the PIP Install -R installation.

DisplayName.Description:
The name of the task is as follows:
The name length does not exceed 256 characters.
Allow numbers, letters, lower strokes (_), English period (.) And short horizontal lines (-).

SuccessPolicy.Description:
The successful strategy of distributed multi -machine tasks is currently only supported by TensorFlow's multi -machine task.
ChiefWorker: When it is specified as this value, as long as the Chief's POD is successful, it is considered that the entire task is successful.
All workers: All workers must be successful to think that the entire task is successful.

MaxRunningTimeMinutes.Description: The longest running time, the unit is: minutes.

Memory.Description: Memory size, the unit is: GB.

WorkspaceId.Description: Work space ID.How to get working space ID, see ListworkSpaces.
