ALIYUN::ROS::WaitCondition.Description: ALIYUN::ROS::WaitCondition is used to wait for signals. You can use ALIYUN::ROS::WaitCondition together with ALIYUN::ROS::WaitConditionHandle to manage the execution process of a stack. When you create an Elastic Compute Service (ECS) instance, a signal is sent during the execution of the user data.

JoinedErrorData.Description: String containing data associated with wait condition error signals sent to the handle.

Data.Description: JSON serialized dict containing data associated with wait condition signals sent to the handle.

ErrorData.Description: JSON serialized dict containing data associated with wait condition error signals sent to the handle.

ShowProgressEvent.Description: Whether to generate progress changed event. Default to Disabled.

Timeout.Description: The number of seconds to wait for the correct number of signals to arrive.

Count.Description: The number of success signals that must be received before the stack creation process continues.

Handle.Description: A reference to the wait condition handle used to signal this wait condition.

ALIYUN::ROS::WaitConditionHandle.Description: ALIYUN::ROS::WaitConditionHandle is used to receive signals. You can use ALIYUN::ROS::WaitConditionHandle together with ALIYUN::ROS::WaitCondition to manage the execution process of a stack. When you create an Elastic Compute Service (ECS) instance, a signal is sent during the execution of the user data.

CurlCli.Description: Convenience attribute, provides curl CLI command prefix, which can be used for signalling handle completion or failure.  You can signal success by adding --data-binary '{"status": "SUCCESS"}' , or signal failure by adding --data-binary '{"status": "FAILURE"}'

WindowsCurlCli.Description: Convenience attribute, provides curl CLI command prefix for Windows, which can be used for signalling handle completion or failure. As Windows does not support curl command, you need to install curl.exe and add it to PATH first. You can signal success by adding --data-binary "{\"status\": \"SUCCESS\"}" , or signal failure by adding --data-binary "{\"status\": \"FAILURE\"}"

Headers.Description: HTTP POST Headers used for signalling handle completion or failure.

URL.Description: HTTP POST URL used for signalling handle completion or failure.

PowerShellCurlCli.Description: Convenience attribute, provides curl CLI command prefix for PowerShell, which can be used for signalling handle completion or failure. As this cmdlet was introduced in PowerShell 3.0, ensure the version of PowerShell satisfies the constraint. (Show the version via $PSVersionTable.PSVersion.) You can signal success by adding -Body '{"status": "SUCCESS"}' , or signal failure by adding -Body '{"status": "FAILURE"}'

Mode.Description:
If set to Increment, all old signals will be deleted before update. In this mode, WaitCondition.Count should reference an incremental value instead of a full value, such as ScalingGroupEnable.ScalingRuleArisExecuteResultNumberOfAddedInstances.

If set to Full, no old signal will be deleted unless Count is set. In this mode, WaitCondition.Count should reference a full value, such as the same value with InstanceGroup.MaxAmount. It is recommended to use this mode with Count.

Default to Full.

Count.Description:
There are 3 preconditions that make Count taking effect:
1.Mode is set to Full.
2.Count >= 0.
3.The id of signal is not specified. If so, it will be a self-increasing integer started from 1. For example, the id of the first signal is 1, the id of the second signal is 2, and so on.

If Count takes effect, signals with id > Count will be deleted before update.
The default value is -1, which means no effect.
It is recommended to quote the same value with WaitCondition.Count.

ALIYUN::SAG::App.Description: ALIYUN::SAG::App is used to create a Smart Access Gateway (SAG) app instance.

OrderId.Description: The ID of the order that you placed to subscribe to the SAG APP instance.

SmartAGId.Description: The ID of the SAG APP instance.

ChargeType.Description:
The billing method of the SAG APP instance. Set the value to PREPAY.
This value indicates that the SAG APP instance is a subscription resource.

UserCount.Description:
The quota of client accounts for the SAG APP instance.
Note The quota must be a positive multiple of 5, for example, 5, 10, and 15.

DataPlan.Description:
The quota of the traffic plan that the system allows each client account to use for
free each month. Unit: GB. Set the value to 5.
Note The system allows each client account to use 5 GB traffic plan for free.

Period.Description:
The subscription period of the SAG APP instance. Unit: months.
Valid values: 1~9, 12, 24, and 36.

AutoPay.Description:
Specifies whether to automatically pay the bills of SAG APP instances. Default value:
false. Valid values:
true: automatically pays the bills of SAG APP instances.
false: does not automatically pay the bills of SAG APP instances.
If you set the parameter to false, after you call this operation, go to Billing Management
of the SAG console to complete the payment, the instance can be created.

ALIYUN::SAG::AppUser.Description: ALIYUN::SAG::AppUser is used to create a client account for a Smart Access Gateway (SAG) app instance.

UserName.Description: <heat.engine.properties.Schema object at 0x7eff88096dd0>

SmartAGId.Description: The ID of the SAG APP instance.

UserName.Description:
The username of the client account. Usernames of client accounts added to the same
SAG APP instance must be unique.
For a client account, if you specify the username, you must also specify the password.

UserMail.Description:
The email address of the user. The username and password are sent to the specified
email address.

Bandwidth.Description: The bandwidth. Unit: Kbit/s. Maximum bandwidth: 2,000 Kbit/s.

SmartAGId.Description: The ID of the SAG APP instance.

ClientIp.Description:
After this feature is enabled, you must specify the IP address of SAG APP. In this
case, SAG APP connects to Alibaba Cloud through the specified IP address.
Note The IP address must fall into the CIDR block of the private network.
After this feature is disabled, an IP address within the CIDR block of the private
network is assigned to SAG APP. Each connection to Alibaba Cloud uses a different
IP address.

Password.Description:
The password used to log on to SAG APP.
For a client account, if you specify the username, you must also specify the password.

ALIYUN::SAG::CloudConnectNetwork.Description: ALIYUN::SAG::CloudConnectNetwork is used to create a Cloud Connect Network (CCN) instance. CNN is a device access matrix composed of Alibaba Cloud distributed Smart Access Gateways (SAGs). You can add multiple SAGs to a CCN instance and then attach the CCN instance to a Cloud Enterprise Network (CEN) instance. In this way, you can connect your local branches to Alibaba Cloud.

CcnId.Description: The ID of the CCN instance.

Description.Description:
The description of the CCN instance.
The description can contain 2 to 256 characters. The description cannot start with http:// or https://.

Tags.Description: Tags to attach to instance. Max support 20 tags to add during create instance. Each tag with two properties Key and Value, and Key is required.

Name.Description:
The name of the CCN instance.
The name can contain 2 to 128 characters including a-z, A-Z, 0-9, chinese, underlines, and hyphens. The name must start with an English letter, but cannot start with http:// or https://.

ALIYUN::SAG::GrantCcnToCen.Description: ALIYUN::SAG::GrantCcnToCen is used to grant permissions on a Cloud Connect Network (CCN) instance to a Cloud Enterprise Network (CEN) instance.

CenInstanceId.Description: The ID of the CEN instance.

CenUid.Description: The ID of the account to which the CEN instance belongs.

CcnInstanceId.Description: The ID of the CCN instance.

CenInstanceId.Description: The ID of the CEN instance.

ALIYUN::SAG::Qos.Description: ALIYUN::SAG::QoS is used to create a quality of service (QoS) policy for a Smart Access Gateway (SAG) instance.

QosId.Description: The ID of the QoS policy.

The name of the QoS policy.
The name must be 2 to 100 characters in length and can contain letters, digits, periods
(.), underscores (_), and hyphens (-). It must start with a letter.

QosDescription.Description:
The description of the QoS policy.

underscores (_), and hyphens (-). It must start with a letter.

SmartAGId.Description: The ID of the SAG instance to which the QoS policy is to be applied.

ALIYUN::SAG::QosCar.Description: ALIYUN::SAG::QosCar is used to create a traffic throttling rule for a quality of service (QoS) policy.

QosCarId.Description: The ID of the traffic throttling policy.

MinBandwidthAbs.Description: The minimum bandwidth. This parameter is required when LimitType is set to Absolute.

Description.Description: The description of the traffic throttling policy.

Priority.Description:
The priority of the traffic throttling policy. A smaller value represents a higher
priority. If policies are assigned the same priority, the one applied the earliest
prevails. Valid values: 1 to 7.

MaxBandwidthPercent.Description:
The maximum percentage that is based on the maximum upstream bandwidth of the SAG
instance.
This parameter is required when LimitType is set to Percent.

MaxBandwidthAbs.Description: The maximum bandwidth. This parameter is required when LimitType is set to Absolute.

QosId.Description: The ID of the QoS policy.

PercentSourceType.Description:
If the policy throttles traffic based on a specified bandwidth percentage, the following
options are available:
CcnBandwidth: Cloud Enterprise Network (CCN) bandwidth.
InternetUpBandwidth: Internet upstream bandwidth.

MinBandwidthPercent.Description:
The minimum percentage that is based on the maximum upstream bandwidth of the SAG
instance.
This parameter is required when LimitType is set to Percent.

LimitType.Description:
The type of the traffic throttling policy. Valid values:
Absolute: throttles traffic by a specific bandwidth range.
Percent: throttles traffic by a specific range of bandwidth percentage.

Name.Description:
The name of the traffic throttling policy. The name must be 2 to 128 characters in
length, and can contain Chinese characters, letters, digits, periods (.), underscores
(_), and hyphens (-).

ALIYUN::SAG::QosPolicy.Description: ALIYUN::SAG::QosPolicy is used to create a traffic classification rule for a quality of service (QoS) policy.

QosPolicyId.Description: The ID of the traffic classification rule.

Description.Description:
The description of the traffic classification rule.
The description must be 1 to 512 characters in length and can contain letters, digits,
underscores (_), and hyphens (-). It must start with a letter.

EndTime.Description:
The time when the traffic classification rule becomes invalid.
Specify the time in the ISO 8601 standard in the YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss+0800 format.
The time must be in UTC+8.

SourcePortRange.Description:
The range of source ports.
Valid values: 1 to 65535 and -1.
Set this parameter in one of the following formats:
1/200: a port range from 1 to 200
80/80: port 80
-1/-1: all ports

SourceCidr.Description:
The range of the source IP addresses.
Specify the value of this parameter in CIDR notation. Example: 192.168.1.0/24.

Priority.Description:
The priority of the traffic throttling policy to which the traffic classification
rule belongs.

StartTime.Description:
The time when the traffic classification rule takes effect.
Specify the time in the ISO 8601 standard in the YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss+0800 format.
The time must be in UTC+8.

DestPortRange.Description:
The range of destination ports.
Valid values: 1 to 65535 and -1.
Set this parameter in one of the following formats:
1/200: a port range from 1 to 200
80/80: port 80
-1/-1: all ports

DpiGroupIds.Description:
The ID of the application group.
You can enter at most 100 application group IDs at a time.
You can call the ListDpiGroups operation to query application group IDs and information about the applications.

Name.Description:
The name of the traffic classification rule.
The name must be 2 to 100 characters in length, and can contain digits, underscores
(_), and hyphens (-). It must start with a letter.

DestCidr.Description:
The range of the destination IP addresses.
Specify the value of this parameter in CIDR notation. Example: 192.168.10.0/24.

DpiSignatureIds.Description:
The ID of the application.
You can enter at most 100 application IDs at a time.
You can call the ListDpiSignatures operation to query application IDs and information about the applications.

QosId.Description: The ID of the QoS policy.

IpProtocol.Description:
The type of the protocol that applies to the traffic classification rule.
The supported protocols provided in this topic are for reference only. The actual
protocols in the console shall prevail.

BuyerMessage.Description: The remarks left by the buyer.

CidrBlock.Description:
The CIDR blocks of terminals in the private network. Make sure that the CIDR blocks
do not overlap with each other.
If the LAN port of the SAG device dynamically assigns IP addresses, IP addresses within
the first CIDR block are assigned to terminals that have the Dynamic Host Configuration
Protocol (DHCP) enabled.

ReceiverTown.Description: The town of the recipient address.

HardWareSpec.Description:
The type of the SAG instance. Valid values:
sag-100wm
sag-1000
sag-vcpe

The name of the SAG instance.

underscores (_), and hyphens (-). It must start with a letter.

ReceiverPhone.Description: The landline phone number of the recipient.

ReceiverCity.Description: The city of the recipient address.

RoutingStrategy.Description:
The policy to advertise routes from the private network to Alibaba Cloud.

dynamic: dynamic routing.

SecurityLockThreshold.Description:
The time that a disconnected SAG device remain locked. The time must be no shorter
than zero second.
Unit: second.

ReceiverAddress.Description: The detailed address of the recipient.

AlreadyHaveSag.Description:
Specifies whether you already have an SAG device. Valid values:
true: yes
false (default): no

HaType.Description:
The deployment mode. Valid values:
no_backup: You buy only one SAG device to connect private networks to Alibaba Cloud.
cold_backup: You buy two SAG devices in active-standby mode. One SAG device serves as an active
device and the other serves as a standby device. Only the active device is connected
to Alibaba Cloud. If the active device is not working as expected, you must manually
perform a switchover.
warm_backup: You buy two SAG devices in active-active mode. Both SAG devices are connected to
Alibaba Cloud. If an active device is not working as expected, a failover is automatically
performed.
Note If you want to create an SAG vCPE instance, set the value to warm_backup.

Period.Description:
The subscription period of the SAG instance. Unit: months.

The bandwidth of the SAG instance.
If you want to create an SAG CPE instance and the model is sag-100wm, valid values of this parameter are 2 to 50. Unit: Mbit/s.
If you want to create an SAG CPE instance and the model is sag-1000, valid values of this parameter are 10 to 500. Unit: Mbit/s.
If you want to create an SAG vCPE instance, valid values of this parameter are 10 to 1000. Unit: Mbit/s.

AutoPay.Description:
Specifies whether to enable auto-payment for the instance. Valid values:
true: yes
false: no
If you set the parameter to false, go to Billing Management to complete the payment
after you call this operation. After you complete the payment, the instance can be
created.

ReceiverDistrict.Description: The district of the recipient address.

Activate.Description: Activate SAG or not. Default is False

ReceiverState.Description: The province of the recipient address.

ReceiverEmail.Description: The email address of the recipient.

ALIYUN::SAS::Instance.Description: ALIYUN::SAS::Instance is used to purchase Security Center.

QuotaForApplicationProtection.Description: The application protection feature can detect attacks on applications and provide self-protection during application runtime. The feature supports simple and convenient O&M and can effectively defend against zero-day and OWASP Top vulnerabilities. The feature is a value-added feature. You are charged based on the number of assets on which the RASP agent is installed. You must configure protection policies after you purchase the feature.

ThreatAnalysis.Description: The threat analysis feature allows you to handle alerts that are generated for assets in the cloud within different accounts and assets of multiple cloud services in a centralized manner. The feature also allows you to handle risks with a few clicks. The feature provides automatic orchestration and response capabilities.

ContainerImageScan.Description: Security Center provides the container image scan feature to protect containers. Security Center can detect CVEs, application vulnerabilities, viruses, and malicious samples and allows you to handle the detected risks. You can configure this parameter based on the number of images or digests. For example, if the number of images or digests that are updated in the previous day is 10, you can set this parameter to 300 for a monthly subscription or to 3650 for a yearly subscription. This is more cost-effective.

AutoRenew.Description: Whether to auto renew the prepay instance.Default: False

MaliciousFileDetectionSDK.Description: The configuration assessment feature detects configuration errors and security risks on cloud services from the following dimensions: identity and permission management, security risks in Alibaba Cloud services, and compliance risks. This ensures the security of the running environment of your cloud services.

VCore.Description: This parameter indicates the number of server vCPUs.

Period.Description:
The subscription period of the firewallIf PeriodUnit is month, the valid range is 1, 3, 6
If periodUnit is year, the valid range is 1, 2, 3

VulnerabilityFixing.Description: The vulnerability fixing feature allows you to fix system vulnerabilities with a few clicks. This improves O&M efficiency. You can separately purchase the vulnerability fixing feature. You are charged based on the number of times that you perform vulnerability fixing.

AutoPay.Description: Whether to auto pay the bill.Default: True

ConfigurationAssessment.Description: The configuration assessment feature detects configuration errors and security risks on cloud services from the following dimensions: identity and permission management, security risks in Alibaba Cloud services, and compliance risks.This ensures the security of the running environment of your cloud services.

LogAnalysis.Description: In response to the requirements of the network security law, which requires logs to be stored for at least 180 days, we recommend that you configure a 40GB log storage each server. Log analysis supports multi-dimensional security logs of cloud assets, out-of-the-box reports, and powerful SQL syntax analysis, so as to monitor business status, troubleshoot attacks, security operations such as traceability and positioning are easier.

ProtectedServers.Description: Authorization is the same as the number of servers you have.

CloudHoneypot.Description: The cloud honeypot feature can capture attacks in a timely and efficient manner. You can use the feature to protect your core assets and detect attacks in attack and defense scenarios.

WebTamperProtection.Description: To ensure that the website information of important systems is not maliciously tampered with, there are bad content such as hanging horses, black chains, illegal implantation of terrorist threats, pornography, etc.

QuotaForVulnerabilityFixing.Description: Specify the quota for vulnerability fixing based on the number of vulnerabilities that you want to fix each month. The quota is equal to the total number of vulnerabilities that you want to fix on all servers regardless of the vulnerability names. For example, if you use Security Center to fix the same vulnerability on 10 servers, the quota is deducted by 10.

AntiRansomware.Description: Security Center provides a comprehensive anti-ransomware solution to protect your business. We recommend that you configure a data protection capacity of 50GB for each server.

PeriodUnit.Description:
The unit of the subscription duration. Valid values:
Month
Year

LoadBalancerId.Description: The id of load balancer.

BackendServers.Description: The collection of attached backend server.

BackendServerList.Description: The comma delimited instance id list.If the property "BackendServers" is setting, this property will be ignored.

LoadBalancerId.Description: The id of load balancer.

BackendServerWeightList.Description: The comma delimited weight list. If no value specified will use 100. If the length is small than "BackendServerList", it will copy the last one to fill the array.If the property "BackendServers" is setting, this property will be ignored.

BackendServers.Description: The list of ECS instance, which will attached to load balancer.

Type.Description: The backend server type. Valid values:ecs: ECS instance (default)eni: Elastic Network Interface (ENI)

ServerId.Description: Need one valid instance id. The instance status should running.

Description.Description: A description of the backend server.

VServerGroupId.Description: The ID of virtual server group.
The ID of virtual server group.

Port.Description: The port of backend server. From 1 to 65535.

AliCloudCertificateName.Description: The name of the Alibaba Cloud certificate.

ResourceGroupId.Description: Resource group id.

Tags.Description: Tags to attach to instance. Max support 20 tags to add during create instance. Each tag with two properties Key and Value, and Key is required.

Certificate.Description: The content of the certificate public key.

AliCloudCertificateId.Description: The ID of the Alibaba Cloud certificate.

ALIYUN::SLB::DomainExtension.Description: ALIYUN::SLB::DomainExtension is used to create a domain extension for an SLB instance.

ListenerPort.Description:
The front-end HTTPS listener port of the Server Load Balancer instance. Valid value:
1-65535

The front-end HTTPS listener port of the Server Load Balancer instance. Valid value:
1-65535

ServerCertificateId.Description: The ID of the certificate corresponding to the domain name.

LoadBalancerId.Description: The ID of Server Load Balancer instance.

ALIYUN::SLB::Listener.Description: ALIYUN::SLB::Listener is used to create a Server Load Balancer (SLB) listener.

LoadBalancerId.Description: The id of load balancer

VServerGroupId.Description: The id of the VServerGroup which use in listener.

Description.Description: The description of the listener.It must be 1 to 80 characters in length and can contain letters, digits, hyphens (-), forward slashes (/), periods (.), and underscores (_). Chinese characters are supported.

ProxyProtocolV2Enabled.Description:
Whether to support carrying the client source address to the backend server through the Proxy Protocol. Value:
true: Yes
false (default): No
Note: Only effective TCP or UDP listener.

Scheduler.Description:
The scheduling algorithm. Valid values:
wrr: Backend servers that have higher weights receive more requests than those that have lower weights.
wlc: Requests are distributed based on the combination of the weights and connections to backend servers. If two backend servers have the same weight, the backend server that has fewer connections receives more requests.
rr: Requests are distributed to backend servers in sequence.
sch: specifies consistent hashing that is based on source IP addresses. Requests from the same source IP address are distributed to the same backend server.
tch: specifies consistent hashing that is based on four factors: source IP address, destination IP address, source port number, and destination port number. Requests that contain the same preceding information are distributed to the same backend server.
Default: wrr

HealthCheck.Description: The properties of health checking setting.

HttpCode.Description: The expect status of health check result. Any answer other than referred status within the timeout period is considered unhealthy.

Switch.Description:
Whether to enable health check. Valid value: on, off.
If value is on, turn on the health check. If value is off, turn off the health checkIf value is not set, the health check is disabled by default, unless any health check items are configured.

UnhealthyThreshold.Description: The number of consecutive health checks failures required,before identified the backend server in Unhealthy status.

Timeout.Description: The amount of time, in seconds, during which no response means a failed health check.

HealthCheckMethod.Description: The health check method used in HTTP or HTTPS health checks. Valid values: head and get.

HealthyThreshold.Description: The number of consecutive health checks successes required,before identified the backend server in Healthy status.

Port.Description: The port being checked. The range of valid ports is 0 through 65535.

Domain.Description: The domain of health check target.

URI.Description: The url of health check target.

HealthCheckType.Description: The type of health check. It takes effect when Protocol=tcp. Valid values: tcp and http. Default value: tcp.

Interval.Description: The approximate interval, unit in seconds, between health checks of an backend server.

IdleTimeout.Description: Specify the idle connection timeout in seconds. Valid value: 1-60 If no request is received during the specified timeout period, Server Load Balancer will temporarily terminate the connection and restart the connection when the next request comes.

LoadBalancerId.Description: The id of load balancer to create listener.

BackendServerPort.Description: Backend server can listen on ports from 1 to 65535.

ConnectionDrainTimeout.Description:
Set the connection graceful interruption timeout. Unit: seconds. Value range: 10-900.
Note: Only effective for TCP listener. When ConnectionDrain is on, this option is required.

Bandwidth.Description: The bandwidth of network, unit in Mbps(Million bits per second). If the specified load balancer with "LOAD_BALANCE_ID" is charged by "paybybandwidth" and is created in classic network, each Listener's bandwidth must be greater than 0 and the sum of all of its Listeners' bandwidth can't be greater than the bandwidth of the load balancer.

Gzip.Description:
Specifies whether to enable Gzip compression to compress specific types of files. Valid values:
on (default): yes
off: no

ServerCertificateId.Description: Server certificate id, for https listener only, this properties is required.

ListenerForward.Description:
Whether to enable HTTP to HTTPS forwarding.
Valid values: on | off. Default value: off.

ForwardPort.Description:
HTTP to HTTPS listening forwarding port.
Default value: 443.

Protocol.Description: The load balancer transport protocol to use for routing: http, https, tcp, or udp.

Tags.Description: Tags to attach to instance. Max support 20 tags to add during create instance. Each tag with two properties Key and Value, and Key is required.

RequestTimeout.Description: Specify the request timeout in seconds. Valid value: 1-180 If no response is received from the backend server during the specified timeout period, Server Load Balancer will stop waiting and send an HTTP 504 error to the client.

ListenerPort.Description: Port for front listener. Range from 0 to 65535.

TLSCipherPolicy.Description: The Transport Layer Security (TLS) security policy. Each security policy contains TLS protocol versions and cipher suites available for HTTPS. It takes effect when Protocol=https.

CACertificateId.Description: CA server certificate id, for https listener only.

AclId.Description:
The ID of the access control associated with the listener to be created.
If the value of the AclStatus parameter is on, this parameter is required.

ConnectionDrain.Description:
Whether to enable graceful connection interruption. Value:on: turn on
off: Not turned on
Note: Only effective TCP listener.

XForwardedFor_SLBID.Description: Optional. Indicates whether to use the SLB-ID header field to obtain the SLB instance ID. Valid values: on | off. Default value: off If you do not set this parameter, the default value is used.

CookieTimeout.Description: The timeout for cookie setting, in seconds. It only take effect while StickySession is setting to 'on' and StickySessionType is setting to 'insert'.

StickySession.Description: The switch of session persistence. Support 'on' and 'off'.

PersistenceTimeout.Description: The timeout number of persistence, in seconds.

XForwardedFor_SLBPORT.Description: Optional. Indicates whether to use the X-Forwarded-Port header field to retrieve the listening ports of the SLB instance. Valid values: on | off. Default value: offIf you do not set this parameter, the default value is used.

XForwardedFor.Description: Use 'X-Forwarded-For' to get real ip of accessor. On for open, off for close.

XForwardedFor_ClientSrcPort.Description: Optional. Indicates whether to use the X-Forwarded-Client-srcport header field to retrieve the port used by a client to connect to the SLB instance. Valid values: on | off. Default value: offIf you do not set this parameter, the default value is used.

XForwardedFor_proto.Description: Optional. Indicates whether to use the X-Forwarded-Proto header field to obtainthe listening protocol used by the SLB instance. Valid values: on | off. Default value: offIf you do not set this parameter, the default value is used.

StickySessionType.Description: The type of session persistence. Depends on parameter StickySession, if it is set to off, this parameter will be ignored.

XForwardedFor_SLBIP.Description: Optional. Indicates whether to use the SLB-IP header field to obtainthe real IP address of a client request.Valid values: on | off. Default value: offIf you do not set this parameter, the default value is used.

PortRange.Description: Port range, only supports TCP or UDP listener. ListenerPort should be 0 when PortRange is specified.

AclStatus.Description:
Indicates whether to enable access control.
Valid values: on | off. Default value: off

MasterSlaveServerGroupId.Description: The id of the MasterSlaveServerGroup which use in listener.

StartListener.Description: Whether start listener after listener created. Default True.

AclType.Description:
The access control type:
* white: Indicates a whitelist. Only requests from IP addresses or CIDR blocks in the selected access control lists are forwarded. This applies to scenarios in which an application only allows access from specific IP addresses.
Enabling a whitelist poses some risks to your services.
After a whitelist is enabled, only the IP addresses in the list can access the listener.
If you enable a whitelist without adding any IP addresses in the list, no requests are forwarded.
* black: Indicates a blacklist. Requests from IP addresses or CIDR blocks in the selected access control lists are not forwarded (that is, they are blocked). This applies to scenarios in which an application only denies access from specific IP addresses.
If you enable a blacklist without adding any IP addresses in the list, all requests are forwarded.

If the value of the AclStatus parameter is on, this parameter is required.

EnableHttp2.Description:
Specifies whether to use HTTP/2. It takes effect when Protocol=https. Valid values:
on: yes
off: no

AclIds.Description:
The ID list of the access controls associated with the listener to be created.
If the value of the AclStatus parameter is on, this parameter is required.AclIds have higher priority than AclId.

ALIYUN::SLB::LoadBalancer.Description: ALIYUN::SLB::LoadBalancer is used to create a Server Load Balancer (SLB) instance.

ResourceGroupId.Description: Resource group id.

VSwitchId.Description: VSwitch id

LoadBalancerId.Description: The id of load balance created.

PayType.Description: The billing method of the instance to be created.

SlaveZoneId.Description: The slave zone id to create load balancer instance.

LoadBalancerSpec.Description: The specification of the Server Load Balancer instance

VpcId.Description: Vpc id

NetworkType.Description: The network type of the load balancer. "vpc" or "classic" network.

Bandwidth.Description: The bandwidth for network

IpAddress.Description: The ip address of the load balancer.

AddressType.Description: The address type of the load balancer. "intranet" or "internet".

MasterZoneId.Description: The master zone id to create load balancer instance.

AutoRenewPeriod.Description:
Automatic renewal cycle, which takes effect when AutoRenew is true, and is required:
When PricingCycle = month, the value range is 1 to 9 or 12, 24, 36.
When PeriodUnit = year, the value range is 1-3.

ResourceGroupId.Description: Resource group id.

InstanceChargeType.Description:
Instance billing method. Valid value:
- **PayBySpec** (default): Pay by spec.
- **PayByCLCU**: billed by usage.

PricingCycle.Description:
Optional. The duration of the Subscription-billed Internet instance to be created.
Valid values: month | year.

AutoRenew.Description: Indicates whether automatic renewal is enabled for the instance. Valid values:- **true**: Automatic renewal is enabled.- **false** (default): Automatic renewal is not enabled. You must renew the instance manually.

VSwitchId.Description: The VSwitch id to create load balancer instance. For VPC network only.

AddressIPVersion.Description: IP version, support 'ipv4' or 'ipv6'. If 'ipv6' is selected, please note that the zone and the specification are supported.

Duration.Description:
Optional. The subscription duration of a Subscription Internet instance.
Valid values:
If PricingCycle is month, the valid range is 1 to 9 or 12, 24, 36, 48, 60.
If PricingCycle is year, the value range is 1 to 5.

AutoPay.Description:
Specifies whether to automatically pay for the subscription Internet-facing CLB instance. Valid values:
- **true**: automatically pays for the CLB instance. After you call this operation, the system automatically completes the payment and creates the CLB instance.- **false** (default): After you call the operation, the order is created but the payment is not completed. You can view the pending order in the console. The CLB instance will not be created until you complete the payment.**Note** This parameter is supported only by subscription instances created on the Alibaba Cloud China site.

PayType.Description:
Optional. The billing method of the instance to be created.
Valid value: PayOnDemand (Pay-As-You-Go) | PrePay (Subscription)

SlaveZoneId.Description: The slave zone id to create load balancer instance.

ModificationProtectionStatus.Description:
NonProtection or empty: means no restriction on modification protection
ConsoleProtection: Modify instance protection status by console
Default value is empty.

InternetChargeType.Description:
The metering method of the Internet-facing CLB instance. Valid values:
- **paybytraffic** (default): If you set the value to paybytraffic, you do not need to specify Bandwidth. Even if you specify Bandwidth, the value does not take effect.
- **paybybandwidth**: pay-by-bandwidth.
**Note** If you set PayType to PayOnDemand and set InstanceChargeType to PayByCLCU, you must set InternetChargeType to paybytraffic.

LoadBalancerSpec.Description:
The specification of the CLB instance. Valid values:
- **slb.s1.small**
- **slb.s2.small**
- **slb.s2.medium**
- **slb.s3.small**
- **slb.s3.medium**
- **slb.s3.large**
**Note** If you do not specify this parameter, a shared-resource CLB instance is created. Shared-resource CLB instances are no longer available for purchase. Therefore, you must specify this parameter.
If InstanceChargeType is set to PayByCLCU, this parameter is invalid and you do not need to specify this parameter.

LoadBalancerName.Description: Name of created load balancer. Length is limited to 1-80 characters, allowed to contain letters, numbers, '-, /, _,.' When not specified, a default name will be assigned.

VpcId.Description: The VPC id to create load balancer instance. For VPC network only.

Bandwidth.Description: The bandwidth for network, unit in Mbps(Mega bit per second). Default is 1. If InternetChargeType is specified as "paybytraffic", this property will be ignore and please specify the "Bandwidth" in ALIYUN::SLB::Listener.

ModificationProtectionReason.Description:
Set the reason for modifying the protection status. The length is 1-80 English or Chinese characters, must start with upper and lower letters or Chinese, and can include numbers, periods (.), underscores (_) and dashes (-).
Only valid when ModificationProtectionStatus is ConsoleProtection.

AddressType.Description:
The network type of the CLB instance. Valid values:
- **internet** (default): After an internet-facing CLB instance is created, the system assigns a public IP address to the CLB instance. Then, the CLB instance can forward requests over the Internet.
- **intranet**: After an internal-facing CLB instance is created, the system assigns a private IP address to the CLB instance. Then, the CLB instance can forward requests only over the internal networks.

Tags.Description: Tags to attach to slb. Max support 5 tags to add during create slb. Each tag with two properties Key and Value, and Key is required.

MasterZoneId.Description: The master zone id to create load balancer instance.

ALIYUN::SLB::LoadBalancerClone.Description: ALIYUN::SLB::LoadBalancerClone is used to clone a Server Load Balancer (SLB) instance.

LoadBalancerId.Description: The id of load balance generated

LoadBalancerName.Description: Name of created load balancer. Length is limited to 1-80 characters, allowed to contain letters, numbers, '-, /, _,.' When not specified, a default name will be assigned.

SourceLoadBalancerId.Description: Source load balancer id to clone

ResourceGroupId.Description: Resource group id.

TagsPolicy.Description:
Solution for handle the tags. If select 'clone', it will clone from source load balancer. If select 'empty' it will not copy tags. If select 'append' it will append the new tags. If select 'replace' it will add new tags.
Default is 'empty'.

InstanceChargeType.Description:
Instance billing method. Value:PayBySpec: Pay by spec.
PayByCLCU: billed by usage.
If not specified, it is same with the source load balancer.

VSwitchId.Description: The new VSwitch ID to create load balancer instance. For VPC network only and the VSwitch should belong to the VPC which source load balancer is located.When not specified, source load balancer VSwitch ID will be used.

BackendServers.Description: The list of ECS instance, which will attached to load balancer.

Type.Description: The backend server type. Valid values:ecs: ECS instance (default)eni: Elastic Network Interface (ENI)

ServerId.Description: Need one valid instance id. The instance status should running.

Description.Description: A description of the backend server.

Weight.Description: The weight of backend server of load balancer. From 0 to 100, 0 means offline. Default is 100.

Tags.Description: Tags to attach to slb. Max support 5 tags to add during create slb. Each tag with two properties Key and Value, and Key is required.

LoadBalancerSpec.Description:
The specification of the load balancer. If not specified, it is same with the source load balancer.
Note If InstanceChargeType is set to PayByCLCU, the LoadBalancerSpec parameter is invalid and you do not need to set this parameter.

BackendServersPolicy.Description: Solution for handle the backend server and weights. If select 'clone', it will clone from source load balancer. If select 'empty' it will not attach any backend servers. If select 'append' it will append the new backend server list to source backed servers. If select 'replace' it will only attach new backend server list. Default is 'clone'.

ALIYUN::SLB::MasterSlaveServerGroup.Description: ALIYUN::SLB::MasterSlaveServerGroup is used to create a primary/secondary server group.

LoadBalancerId.Description: The ID of the Server Load Balancer instance.

MasterSlaveServerGroupName.Description: The name of the active/standby server group.

MasterSlaveBackendServers.Description:
A list of active/standby server group.
An active/standby server group can only contain two backend servers.

ServerType.Description: The identity of backend server. Could be "Master" (default) or "Slave"

Type.Description:
Specify the type of backend server. This parameter must be of the STRING type. Valid values:
ecs: an ECS instance
eni: an elastic network interface (ENI).

ServerIp.Description: The IP of ECS or ENI.

Port.Description: The port used by backend server. From 1 to 65535

Weight.Description: The weight of backend server of load balancer. From 0 to 100, 0 means offline. Default is 100.

ALIYUN::SLB::Rule.Description: ALIYUN::SLB::Rule is used to add forwarding rules to an HTTP or HTTPS listener.

Rules.Description: A list of forwarding rules. Each element of rules contains "RuleId".

ListenerPort.Description:
The front-end HTTPS listener port of the Server Load Balancer instance. Valid value:
1-65535

VServerGroupId.Description: The ID of the VServer group associated with the forwarding rule.

AdvancedSettings.Description: The advanced settings of the rule.

CookieTimeout.Description: The timeout period of a cookie. Unit: seconds.

Cookie.Description:
The cookie that is configured on the server.
The cookie must be 1 to 200 characters in length and can contain only ASCII characters and digits. It cannot contain commas (,), semicolons (;), or space characters. It cannot start with a dollar sign ($).

HealthCheckInterval.Description: The interval between two consecutive health checks. Unit: seconds. Valid values: 1 to 50.

UnhealthyThreshold.Description: The number of times that a healthy backend server must consecutively fail health checks before it is declared unhealthy. In this case, the health status is changed from success to fail.

HealthCheckURI.Description: The URI that is used for health checks.

Scheduler.Description:
The scheduling algorithm. Valid values:
wrr: Backend servers with higher weights receive more requests than those with lower weights.
rr: Requests are distributed to backend servers in sequence.

HealthCheck.Description:
Specifies whether to enable the health check feature. Valid values:
on: yes
off: no

HealthCheckTimeout.Description: The timeout period of a health check response. If a backend server, such as an Elastic Compute Service (ECS) instance, does not return a health check response within the specified timeout period, the server fails the health check. Unit: seconds. Valid values: 1 to 300.

StickySession.Description:
Specifies whether to enable session persistence. Valid values:
on: yes
off: no

HealthCheckConnectPort.Description: The port that is used for health checks. Valid values: 1 to 65535.

HealthyThreshold.Description: The number of times that an unhealthy backend server must consecutively pass health checks before it is declared healthy. In this case, the health status is changed from fail to success.

ListenerSync.Description:
Specifies whether to use the scheduling algorithm, session persistence, and health check configurations of the listener. Valid values:
on: uses the configurations of the listener.
off: does not use the configurations of the listener. You can customize the health check and session persistence configurations for the forwarding rule.

HealthCheckDomain.Description:
The domain name that is used for health checks. Valid values:
$_ip: the private IP address of a backend server. If you do not set this parameter or set the parameter to $_ip, the SLB instance uses the private IP address of each backend server for health checks.
domain: The domain name must be 1 to 80 characters in length, and can contain letters, digits, periods (.), and hyphens (-).

StickySessionType.Description:
The method that is used to handle a cookie. Valid values:
insert: inserts a cookie.
server: rewrites a cookie.

HealthCheckHttpCode.Description:
The HTTP status code for a successful health check. Multiple HTTP status codes are separated by commas (,).
Valid values: http_2xx, http_3xx, http_4xx, and http_5xx.

RuleName.Description: The name of the forwarding rule.

LoadBalancerId.Description: The ID of Server Load Balancer instance.

ListenerProtocol.Description: The frontend protocol that is used by the SLB instance.

Ciphers.Description: The supported cipher suites, which are determined by the TLS protocol version.

TLSPolicyName.Description: The name of the TLS policy.

CreateTime.Description: Creation time.

TlsVersions.Description: The version of the TLS protocol.

Ciphers.Description:
The supported cipher suites, which are determined by the TLS protocol version. You can specify at most 32 cipher suites.TLS 1.0 and TLS 1.1 support the following cipher suites:
ECDHE-ECDSA-AES128-SHA
ECDHE-ECDSA-AES256-SHA
ECDHE-RSA-AES128-SHA
ECDHE-RSA-AES256-SHA
AES128-SHA
AES256-SHA
DES-CBC3-SHA
TLS 1.2 supports the following cipher suites:
ECDHE-ECDSA-AES128-SHA
ECDHE-ECDSA-AES256-SHA
ECDHE-RSA-AES128-SHA
ECDHE-RSA-AES256-SHA
AES128-SHA
AES256-SHA
DES-CBC3-SHA
ECDHE-ECDSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256
ECDHE-ECDSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384
ECDHE-ECDSA-AES128-SHA256
ECDHE-ECDSA-AES256-SHA384
ECDHE-RSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256
ECDHE-RSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384
ECDHE-RSA-AES128-SHA256
ECDHE-RSA-AES256-SHA384
AES128-GCM-SHA256
AES256-GCM-SHA384
AES128-SHA256
AES256-SHA256
TLS 1.3 supports the following cipher suites:
TLS_AES_128_GCM_SHA256
TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384
TLS_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256
TLS_AES_128_CCM_SHA256
TLS_AES_128_CCM_8_SHA256

TLSPolicyName.Description: The name of the TLS policy. The name must be 1 to 200 characters in length, and can contain letters, digits, periods (.), underscores (_), and hyphens (-).

TlsVersions.Description: The version of the TLS protocol.

*.Description: The version of the TLS protocol. Valid values: TLSv1.0, TLSv1.1, TLSv1.2, and TLSv1.3. You can specify at most four TLS versions.

ALIYUN::SLB::VServerGroup.Description: ALIYUN::SLB::VServerGroup is used to create a server group and attach backend servers to a Server Load Balancer (SLB) instance.

LoadBalancerId.Description: The id of load balancer.

BackendServers.Description: Backend server list in this VServerGroup.

LoadBalancerId.Description: The id of load balancer.

BackendServers.Description: The list of a combination of ECS Instance-Port-Weight.Same ecs instance with different port is allowed, but same ecs instance with same port isn't.

Type.Description:
The instance type of the backend server. This parameter must be set to a string. Valid values:
ecs: ECS instance. This is the default value.
eni: ENI.
eci: ECI.

Description.Description: The description of the backend server. The description must be 1 to 80 characters in length, and can contain letters, digits, hyphens (-), forward slashes (/), periods (.), and underscores (_).

ServerId.Description: The ID of the backend server. You can specify the ID of an Elastic Compute Service (ECS) instance,an elastic network interface (ENI) or elastic container instance (ECI).

ServerIp.Description: The IP address of an ECS instance, ENI or ECI

Port.Description: The port of backend server. From 1 to 65535.

Weight.Description: The weight of backend server of load balancer. From 0 to 100, 0 means offline. Default is 100.

Tags.Description: Tags to attach to instance. Max support 20 tags to add during create instance. Each tag with two properties Key and Value, and Key is required.

ALIYUN::SLS::Alert.Description: ALIYUN::SLS::Alert is used to create an alert rule.

Name.Description: Alert name.

Project.Description:
Project name:
1. Only supports lowercase letters, numbers, hyphens (-) and underscores (_).
2. Must start and end with lowercase letters and numbers.
3. The name length is 3-63 characters.

Description.Description: Description of the alert.

Throttling.Description: Notification interval, default is no interval.

Condition.Description:
The condition that is required to trigger an alert. 
Log Service triggers an alert if the trigger condition is met. 
For example, you can set the trigger condition to pv%100 > 0 && uv > 0.

Severity.Description:
The alarm level when there is no data to trigger the alarm. Valid values:
2: Report
4: Low
6: Medium
8: High
10: Critical.

Condition.Description: It is triggered when any piece of data in the result of judging the Cartesian product satisfies the Condition. After grouping, it indicates the data trigger condition for each group, and an empty string indicates that any data row is satisfied.

CountCondition.Description: Alarm expression, indicating how much data meets the alarm condition.

NoDataFire.Description: Whether to trigger an alarm if there is no data, the default is false.

Type.Description:
This topic describes how to configure a notification method. 
Log Service can send alert notifications by using one or more methods. 
Available notification methods include emails, DingTalk chatbot webhooks, 
custom webhooks, and Alibaba Cloud Message Center.

ServiceUri.Description: The webhook URL of the DingTalk chatbot.

Content.Description: The content of an alert notification

NotifyThreshold.Description:
The notification threshold, 
which will not be notified until the number of triggers is reached.

Type.Description:
Grouping type.
no_group: no grouping
labels_auto: autocustom: custom.

Fields.Description: The fields of group. Fill in the empty list when not group. No fill when group automatically. Fill required when group in custom.

NoDataSeverity.Description:
The alarm level when there is no data to trigger the alarm. Valid values:
2: Report
4: Low
6: Medium
8: High
10: Critical.

Type.Description: Configuration type.

*.Description: An annotation is a fixed and non-identifying attribute of an alert. You can quote annotations by using alert ID:${alert_id}, alert name:${alert_name}, or the field name after the set operations:${field name}. Annotations can be quoted in alert templates by using ${annotations.annotation name}.

JoinConfigurations.Description: The list of Join conditions when multiple tables are joined. For example, 3 tables join, and 2 joinConfigurations are passed in.

Condition.Description: Condition for a set operation. Not required when using Cartesian product.

Type.Description: The type of set operation join.

ActionPolicyId.Description: The ID of action policy. It is useful when an alert policy references a dynamic action policy.

RepeatInterval.Description: Repeat interval. The format is number with suffix s/m/h.

Store.Description:
When StoreType is log or metric, it indicates the LogStore to be queried.
When StoreType is meta, it indicates the ResourceName to be queried.

StoreType.Description:
Log store type. Valid values:
log: sls query analysis statement
metric: sls time series data
meta: query metastore.

SendResolved.Description: Whether to notify when the alarm is restored, the default is false.

Schedule.Description:
The interval at which Log Service evaluates the alert rule. 
Note During an alert rule evaluation, if a query returns more than 100 log entries, 
 Log Service checks only the first 100 log entries.

DisplayName.Description: Alert name display in console. The name length is 1-64 characters.

Name.Description: Alert name.

ALIYUN::SLS::ApplyConfigToMachineGroup.Description: ALIYUN::SLS::ApplyConfigToMachineGroup is used to apply Log Service configurations to machine groups.

GroupName.Description: Apply config to the group name

ConfigName.Description: Apply config to the config name

ProjectName.Description: Apply config to the project name.

DisplayName.Description: Name of SLS log audit.

VpcFlowEnabled.Description: Flow log of VPC. Default false.

RdsPerfEnabled.Description: RDS perf log switch. Default false.

RdsPerfTiEnabled.Description: Threat Intelligence of rds perf log.

K8sIngressTtl.Description: K8s Ingress log centralization ttl. Default 180.

OssSyncEnabled.Description: OSS synchronization to central configuration switch. Default true.

BastionEnabled.Description: Fortress machine operation log switch.Default true.

RdsEnabled.Description: RDS audit log switch. Default true.

RedisSyncTtl.Description: Redis sync to center switch. Default 180.

SasSessionEnabled.Description: Cloud security center network session log switch.Default false.

AlbAccessEnabled.Description: Specifies whether to collect ALB access log. Default false.

AlbSyncEnabled.Description: ALB synchronization to central configuration switch. Default true.

RdsSlowEnabled.Description: RDS slow log switch. Default false.

SasDnsQueryEnabled.Description: Specifies whether to collect DNS query logs. Default false.

SasSnapshotPortEnabled.Description: Cloud Security Center Port Snapshot Switch. Default false.

CloudconfigChangeEnabled.Description: CloudConfig change log switch. Default false.

RdsSlowTtl.Description: Rds slow log centralization ttl. Default 180.

PolardbEnabled.Description: POLARDB audit log switch. Default true.

SasSnapshotProcessEnabled.Description: Cloud Security Center process snapshot switch. Default false.

VpcFlowCollectionPolicy.Description: VPC flow log collection policy script. Default empty.

SlbSyncTtl.Description: Slb sync to center switch. Default 180.

DdosCooAccessEnabled.Description: Ddos access log switch. Default false.

SasSecurityVulEnabled.Description: Cloud Security Center Vulnerability Log Switch.Default false.

CpsEnabled.Description: Mobile push log switch. Default true.

DdosBgpAccessEnabled.Description: Anti-DDoS (Origin) access log switch. Default false.

VpcSyncTtl.Description: VPC synchronization to central TTL. Default 180.

OssAccessEnabled.Description: Access log switch of OSS. Default true.

PolardbPerfTiEnabled.Description: Threat Intelligence of POLARDB perf log.

SasLocalDnsEnabled.Description: Cloud security center local DNS log switch. Default false.

OssAccessTtl.Description: Access log TTL of OSS. Default 180.

SasHttpEnabled.Description: Cloud Security Center WEB access log switch. Default false.

CloudfirewallEnabled.Description: Cloud firewall log switch. Default true.

DnsIntranetEnabled.Description: Specifies whether to collect intranet Alibaba Cloud DNS (DNS) logs. Default false.

CloudfirewallVpcTtl.Description: The retention period of Cloud Firewall VPC firewall traffic logs in the central Logstore. Default 180.

AlbAccessCollectionPolicy.Description: ALB access log collection policy script. Default empty.

DnsSyncTtl.Description: The retention period of intranet DNS logs in the central Logstore. Default 180.

DdosDipAccessEnabled.Description: Anti-DDoS Premium access log switch. Default false.

DrdsSyncTtl.Description: DRDS sync to center ttl. Default 180.

SasLoginEnabled.Description: Cloud security center login flow log switch. Default false.

K8sIngressEnabled.Description: K8s Ingress log switch. Default false.

RdsErrorEnabled.Description: Specifies whether to collect RDS error log. Default false.

ActiontrailEnabled.Description: Notification type. Support Email, SMS, DingTalk. Default true.

DrdsSyncEnabled.Description: DRDS sync to center switch. Default true.

ApigatewayEnabled.Description: API Gateway Log Switch. Default true.

ALIYUN::SLS::LogtailConfig.Description: ALIYUN::SLS::LogtailConfig is used to configure Logtail properties for data collection.

LogtailConfigName.Description:
Logtail config name:
1. Only supports lowercase letters, numbers, hyphens (-) and underscores (_).
2. Must start and end with lowercase letters and numbers.
3. The name length is 3-63 characters.

LogstoreName.Description:
Logstore name:
1. Only supports lowercase letters, numbers, hyphens (-) and underscores (_).
2. Must start and end with lowercase letters and numbers.
3. The name length is 3-63 characters.

ProjectName.Description:
Project name:
1. Only supports lowercase letters, numbers, hyphens (-) and underscores (_).
2. Must start and end with lowercase letters and numbers.
3. The name length is 3-63 characters.

RawConfigData.Description:
The format is the same as the response of SLS API GetConfig.
Either CloneFrom or RawConfigData must be specified. If CloneFrom and RawConfigData are both specified, logtail config data will be merged from both with RawConfigData first.
configName, outputType, outputDetail in data will be ignored.For example:
{
    "configName": "test-logtail-config",
    "createTime": 1574843554,
    "inputDetail": {
        "acceptNoEnoughKeys": false,
        "adjustTimezone": false,
        "advanced": {
            "force_multiconfig": false
        },
        "autoExtend": true,
        "delayAlarmBytes": 0,
        "delaySkipBytes": 0,
        "discardNonUtf8": false,
        "discardUnmatch": false,
        "dockerExcludeEnv": {},
        "dockerExcludeLabel": {},
        "dockerFile": false,
        "dockerIncludeEnv": {},
        "dockerIncludeLabel": {},
        "enableRawLog": false,
        "enableTag": false,
        "fileEncoding": "utf8",
        "filePattern": "test.log*",
        "filterKey": [],
        "filterRegex": [],
        "key": [
            "time",
            "logger",
            "level",
            "request_id",
            "user_id",
            "region_id",
            "content"
        ],
        "localStorage": true,
        "logPath": "/var/log/test",
        "logTimezone": "",
        "logType": "delimiter_log",
        "maxDepth": 100,
        "maxSendRate": -1,
        "mergeType": "topic",
        "preserve": true,
        "preserveDepth": 1,
        "priority": 0,
        "quote": "\u0001",
        "sendRateExpire": 0,
        "sensitive_keys": [],
        "separator": ",,,",
        "shardHashKey": [],
        "tailExisted": false,
        "timeFormat": "",
        "timeKey": "",
        "topicFormat": "none"
    },
    "inputType": "file",
    "lastModifyTime": 1574843554,
    "logSample": "2019-11-27 10:48:23,160,,,MAIN,,,INFO,,,98DCC51D-BE5D-49C7-B3FD-37B2BAEFB296,,,123456789,,,cn-hangzhou,,,this is a simple test.",
    "outputDetail": {
        "endpoint": "cn-hangzhou-intranet.log.aliyuncs.com",
        "logstoreName": "test-logstore",
        "region": "cn-hangzhou"
    },
    "outputType": "LogService"
}

CloneFrom.Description:
Clone logtail config data from existing logtail config.
Either CloneFrom or RawConfigData must be specified. If CloneFrom and RawConfigData are both specified, logtail config data will be merged from both with RawConfigData first.

LogtailConfigName.Description:
Logtail config name:
1. Only supports lowercase letters, numbers, hyphens (-) and underscores (_).
2. Must start and end with lowercase letters and numbers.
3. The name length is 3-63 characters.

ProjectName.Description:
Project name:
1. Only supports lowercase letters, numbers, hyphens (-) and underscores (_).
2. Must start and end with lowercase letters and numbers.
3. The name length is 3-63 characters.

The lifecycle of log in the metrice store in days.
Allowed Values: 1-3000, default to 30.

The number of Shards.
Allowed Values: 1-10, default to 2.

ProjectName.Description: The project name of SLS.

ExportName.Description: The name of the export job.

Description.Description: The description of the export job. It could be 0 to 256 characters in length.

Configuration.Description: The configuration of the export job.

ToTime.Description: The end time of the time range.

BufferInterval.Description: The shipping time. The maximum interval at which data is shipped. Valid values: 300 to 900. Unit: seconds.

ContentType.Description: The storage format. You can store data in the Parquet format for data analysis. Compared with data stored in the CSV or JSON format, data stored in the Parquet format can be scanned at a higher efficiency.You are charged more fees when you ship data in the Parquet format than in the CSV or JSON format. Select a storage format for data shipping based on your business requirements.

ContentDetail.Description: The content detail. If ContentType=json, the default value is {"EnableTag": false}.

PathFormat.Description: The partition format is used to generate subdirectories. A subdirectory is dynamically generated based on the shipping time. The default partition format is %Y/%m/%d/%H/%M. Example: 2017/01/23/12/00. Note that the partition format cannot start with a forward slash (/). For more information about how to integrate with the compute engines of E-MapReduce such as Hive and Impala to query and analyze data

Prefix.Description: The prefix of the OSS object name.

PathFormatType.Description: The partition format type. Only support time.

RoleArn.Description: Used to control permissions of writing data to OSS and reading data in Logstores. Example: acs:ram::13234:role/aliyunlogdefaultrole.

BufferSize.Description: The shipping size. The value of this parameter determines the maximum size of raw log data that is shipped and stored in an object. Unit: MB. If the size of log data that you want to ship reaches the specified value, a shipping job is automatically created.

TimeZone.Description: The time zone. Partition paths vary based on time zones. The value should be -1200 to +1400. For example, +0800.

Suffix.Description: The suffix of the OSS object name.

Endpoint.Description: The endpoint of the OSS bucket.

DelaySeconds.Description:
The shipping latency. The period of time after which data is shipped. Valid values: 900 to 63244800. Unit: seconds.
Note: Do not specify a latency that exceeds the data retention period of the Logstore. We recommend that you reserve a buffer period of a few days for the latency. Otherwise, data loss may occur.

Bucket.Description: The name of the OSS bucket.

CompressionType.Description: The compression method of OSS data. Valid values: none, snappy, gzip, and zstd. The value none indicates that raw data is not compressed. The value snappy, gzip, or zstd indicates that a specified algorithm is used to compress data, which can reduce the storage space usage of OSS buckets. The compression methods vary based on storage formats.

Logstore.Description: The logstore name of the project.

FromTime.Description: The start time of the time range.

RoleArn.Description: Used to control permissions of writing data to OSS and reading data in Logstores. Example: acs:ram::13234:role/aliyunlogdefaultrole.

ProjectName.Description: The project name of SLS.

DisplayName.Description: The display name of the export job. It must be 4 to 100 characters in length.

ExportName.Description: The name of the export job. This value should be unique. It must be 2 to 64 characters in length and can contain lowercase letters, digits, hyphens (-), and underscores (_). It must start and end with a lowercase letter or a digit.

*.Description:
Type of service log that needs to be activated. Allowed values: 
DetailedLogs: If you turn on the Detailed Logs switch and select a project, a Logstore and a dashboard are automatically created in the project. You are charged for using the Logstore.
ImportantLogs: If you turn on Important Logs and select a project, a Logstore is automatically created in the project to store the logs, such as consumption delay logs of consumer groups and Logtail heartbeat logs. The Logstore is provided free of charge. 
JobOperationalLogs: A Logstore named internal-diagnostic_log is created in the specified project to store job operational logs. The operational logs of data import jobs, Scheduled SQL jobs, and data shipping jobs are recorded. The Logstore is provided free of charge.

ProjectName.Description: The name of the project that needs to be activated. If it has been activated, it will be reactivated again.

ALIYUN::ThreatDetection::AntiBruteForceR.Description: ALIYUN::ThreatDetection::AntiBruteForceRule is used to create a defense rule against brute-force attacks.

DefaultRule.Description:
Specifies whether to set the defense rule as the default rule. 
Valid values:
- true: yes
- false: no

AntiBruteForceRuleName.Description: The name of the defense rule.

ForbiddenTime.Description: The period of time during which logons from an account are not allowed. Unit: minutes.

AntiBruteForceRuleId.Description: The ID of the defense rule.

UuidList.Description: The UUIDs of the server to which the defense rule is applied.

FailCount.Description: The threshold for the number of failed user logins when the brute-force defense rule takes effect.

Span.Description: The period of time during which logon failures from an account are measured. Unit: minutes. If Span is set to 10, the defense rule takes effect when the logon failures measured within 10 minutes reaches the specified threshold. The IP addresses of attackers cannot be used to log on to the server within the specified period of time.

DefaultRule.Description:
Specifies whether to set the defense rule as the default rule. 
Valid values:
- true: yes
- false: no

AntiBruteForceRuleName.Description: The name of the defense rule.

ForbiddenTime.Description:
The period of time during which logons from an account are not allowed.
Unit: minutes. Valid values:
- 5: 5 minutes
- 15: 15 minutes
- 30: 30 minutes
- 60: 1 hour
- 120: 2 hours
- 360: 6 hours
- 720: 12 hours
- 1440: 24 hours
- 10080: 7 days
- 52560000: permanent

UuidList.Description: The UUIDs of the servers to which you want to apply the defense rule.

*.Description: The UUID of the server that configures the brute-force defense rule.

FailCount.Description:
The maximum number of failed logon attempts from an account. 
Valid values: 2, 3, 4, 5, 10, 50, 80, and 100.

Span.Description:
The maximum period of time during which failed logon attempts from an account can occur.
Unit: minutes. Valid values:
- 1
- 2
- 5
- 10
- 15

ALIYUN::VOD::EditingProject.Description: ALIYUN::VOD::EditingProject is used to create an online editing project.

EditingProjectName.Description: The name of the online editing project.

Timeline.Description: The timeline of the online editing project.

ModifiedTime.Description:
The last time when the online editing project was modified.
The time follows the ISO 8601 standard in the yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ format. The time is displayed in UTC.

CreateTime.Description:
The time when the online editing project was created.
The time follows the ISO 8601 standard in the yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ format. The time is displayed in UTC.

Title.Description: The title of the online editing project.

EditingProjectId.Description: The ID of the online editing project.

EditingProjectName.Description: The name of the online editing project.

Timeline.Description:
The timeline of the online editing project, in JSON format.
If you do not specify this parameter, an empty timeline is created and the duration of the online editing project is zero.

Title.Description: The title of the online editing project.

ALIYUN::VOD::MessageCallback.Description: ALIYUN::VOD::MessageCallback is used to configure the callback method, callback URL, and event types for an event notification.

MnsEndpoint.Description:
This parameter needs to be set when the callback method is MNS for the 
message queue public network endpoint. You can log in to the message service 
console and click the Get Endpoint button in the upper right corner to get it.

CallbackUrl.Description:
Callback address. When the callback method is HTTP, 
this parameter needs to be set. The length of the callback address 
URL cannot exceed 256 bytes, and setting multiple callback addresses is not supported.

AuthSwitch.Description:
The authentication switch of the HTTP callback, 
this parameter is valid when the callback method is set to HTTP.

AppId.Description:
App ID. If it is not passed, it is the ID of the default 
application of the system, with a fixed value: app-1000000.

EventTypeList.Description:
Callback event type. When the value is empty, all message notifications are turned off, 
and when the value is ALL, all message notifications are turned on. 
You can also specify to enable certain message notifications, 
and use a comma (,) to separate multiple event types.

MnsQueueName.Description:
The name of the message queue, which can be viewed in the queue 
list by logging in to the message service console. 
When the callback method is MNS, this parameter needs to be set.

AuthKey.Description:
Authentication Key, up to 32 characters, must contain both uppercase 
and lowercase letters and numbers. This parameter can be set when the callback method is HTTP.

ALIYUN::VOD::Storage.Description: ALIYUN::VOD::Storage is used to add an Object Storage Service (OSS) bucket in ApsaraVideo VOD (VOD).

Type.Description: Storage type.

ResourceGroupId.Description: The ID of the resource group.

CreateTime.Description: The creation time of the storage.

ALIYUN::VPC::AnycastEIP.Description: ALIYUN::VPC::AnycastEIP is used to create an Anycast elastic IP address (Anycast EIP).

Name.Description: Anycast EIP instance name
